source_text: He died in Osaka on Tuesday.
target_text: Han døde i Osaka tirsdag.

source_text: As well as a former Olympic and World champion, Saito was the All Japan Judo Federation training committee chairman at the time of his death.
target_text: Som tidligere olympisk og verdensmester var Saito også formand for All Japan Judo Federation træningsudvalget på tidspunktet for sin død.

source_text: At least 100 people had attended the party, in order to celebrate the first anniversary of a couple whose wedding was held last year.
target_text: Mindst 100 mennesker var til stede på festen for at fejre det første års jubilæum af et par, hvis bryllup blev afholdt sidste år.

source_text: A formal anniversary event was scheduled for a later date, officials said.
target_text: Et officielt jubilæumsarrangement var planlagt til et senere tidspunkt, sagde embedsmændene.

source_text: The couple had married in Texas one year ago and came to Buffalo to celebrate with friends and relatives.
target_text: Parret havde giftet sig i Texas for et år siden og kom til Buffalo for at fejre med venner og slægtninge.

source_text: The 30-year-old husband, who was born in Buffalo, was one of the four killed in the shooting, but his wife was not hurt.
target_text: Den 30-årige mand, der blev født i Buffalo, var en af de fire dræbte i skyderiet, men hans kone blev ikke såret.

source_text: Karno is a well-known but controversial English tutor who taught under Modern Education and King's Glory who claimed to have 9,000 students at the peak of his career.
target_text: Karno er en kendt, men kontroversiel engelskunderviser, der underviste under Modern Education og King's Glory, som hævdede at have 9.000 studerende på toppen af sin karriere.

source_text: In his notes he used words which some parents considered coarse, and he reportedly used profanity in class.
target_text: I sine notater brugte han ord, som nogle forældre betragtede som grove, og han angiveligt brugte profani i klassen.

source_text: Modern Education accused him of printing large advertisements on buses without authorisation and lying by saying that he was the chief English tutor.
target_text: Modern Education anklagede ham for at have trykt store reklamer på busser uden tilladelse og for at have løjet ved at sige at han var engelsklæreren.

source_text: He has also been accused previously of copyright infringement, but was not charged.
target_text: Han er også tidligere blevet anklaget for overtrædelse af ophavsretten, men blev ikke anklaget.

source_text: A former student said that he 'used slang in class, taught dating skills in notes, and was just like the students' friend.'
target_text: En tidligere elev sagde at han 'brugte slang i klassen, lærte dating færdigheder i notater og var ligesom elevernes ven'.

source_text: During the last three decades, despite officially remaining a communist state, China has developed a market economy.
target_text: I løbet af de sidste tre årtier har Kina, på trods af at den stadig er en kommunistisk stat, udviklet en markedsøkonomi.

source_text: The first economic reforms were made under the leadership of Deng Xiaoping.
target_text: De første økonomiske reformer blev foretaget under ledelse af Deng Xiaoping.

source_text: Since then, China's economic size has grown by 90 times.
target_text: Siden da er Kinas økonomiske størrelse vokset 90 gange.

source_text: For the first time, last year China exported more cars than Germany and surpassed the United States as the biggest market for this industry.
target_text: For første gang eksporterede Kina sidste år flere biler end Tyskland og overgik USA som det største marked for denne industri.

source_text: China's GDP could be larger than the United States within two decades.
target_text: Kinas BNP kan være større end USA inden for to årtier.

source_text: Tropical Storm Danielle, fourth named storm of the 2010 Atlantic hurricane season, has formed in the eastern Atlantic Ocean.
target_text: Tropisk storm Danielle, den fjerde navngivede storm i den atlantiske orkan sæson 2010, har dannet sig i det østlige Atlanterhavet.

source_text: The storm, located approximately 3,000 miles from Miami, Florida, has maximum sustained winds of 40 mph (64 kph).
target_text: Stormen, der ligger ca. 3.000 miles fra Miami, Florida, har maksimal vedvarende vinde på 40 mph (64 km/t).

source_text: Scientists at the National Hurricane Center predict that Danielle will strengthen to a hurricane by Wednesday.
target_text: Forskere ved National Hurricane Center forudser, at Danielle vil styrke sig til en orkan ved onsdag.

source_text: As the storm is far from landfall, it remains difficult to assess potential impact to the United States or Caribbean.
target_text: Da stormen er langt fra land, er det stadig vanskeligt at vurdere den potentielle indvirkning på USA eller Caribien.

source_text: Born in the Croatian capital, Zagreb, Bobek gained fame while playing for Partizan Belgrade.
target_text: Bobek blev født i den kroatiske hovedstad Zagreb, og fik berømmelse, mens han spillede for Partizan Belgrad.

source_text: He joined them in 1945 and stayed until 1958.
target_text: Han sluttede sig til dem i 1945 og blev der indtil 1958.

source_text: During his time with the team, he scored 403 goals in 468 appearances.
target_text: I løbet af sin tid med holdet scorede han 403 mål i 468 optrædener.

source_text: No one else has ever made more appearances or scored more goals for the club than Bobek.
target_text: Ingen andre har nogensinde gjort flere optrædener eller scoret flere mål for klubben end Bobek.

source_text: In 1995 he was voted the best player in Partizan's history.
target_text: I 1995 blev han valgt til den bedste spiller i Partizan historie.

source_text: The celebrations started with a special show by the world-renowned group Cirque du Soleil.
target_text: Festen begyndte med et særligt show af den verdensberømte gruppe Cirque du Soleil.

source_text: It was followed by the Istanbul State Symphony Orchestra, a Janissary band, and the singers Fatih Erkoç and Müslüm Gürses.
target_text: Det blev fulgt af Istanbul State Symphony Orchestra, et Janissary band, og sangerne Fatih Erkoç og Müslüm Gürses.

source_text: Then Whirling Dervishes took to the stage.
target_text: Så tog Whirling Dervishes op på scenen.

source_text: Turkish diva Sezen Aksu performed with the Italian tenor Alessandro Safina and Greek singer Haris Alexiou.
target_text: Den tyrkiske diva Sezen Aksu optrådte med den italienske tenor Alessandro Safina og den græske sanger Haris Alexiou.

source_text: To finish, Turkish dance group Fire of Anatolia performed the show "Troy".
target_text: Til slut udførte den tyrkiske dansgruppe Fire of Anatolia showet "Troy".

source_text: Peter Lenz, a 13-year-old motorcycle racer, has died after being involved in a crash at the Indianapolis Motor Speedway.
target_text: Peter Lenz, en 13-årig motorcykelridder, er død efter at have været involveret i en ulykke på Indianapolis Motor Speedway.

source_text: While on his warm-up lap, Lenz fell off his bike, and was then struck by fellow racer Xavier Zayat.
target_text: Mens han var på sin opvarmningsrunde faldt Lenz fra sin cykel, og blev derefter ramt af kollega Xavier Zayat.

source_text: He was immediately attended to by the on-track medical staff and transported to a local hospital where he later died.
target_text: Han blev straks behandlet af det medicinske personale på banen og transporteret til et lokalt hospital, hvor han senere døde.

source_text: Zayat was unhurt in the accident.
target_text: Zayat var uskadt i ulykken.

source_text: Regarding the global financial situation, Zapatero continued by saying that "the financial system is a part of the economy, a crucial part.
target_text: Med hensyn til den globale finansielle situation fortsatte Zapatero med at sige, at "det finansielle system er en del af økonomien, en afgørende del.

source_text: We have a year-long financial crisis, which has had its most acute moment in the past two months, and I think now the financial markets are beginning to recover."
target_text: Vi har haft en års lang finanskris, som har haft sit mest akutte øjeblik i de sidste to måneder, og jeg tror nu, at finansmarkederne begynder at genoprette sig".

source_text: Last week, Naked News announced that it would dramatically increase its international language mandate to news reporting, with three new broadcasts.
target_text: Sidste uge annoncerede Naked News, at den drastisk ville øge sit internationale sprogmandat til nyhedsrapportering, med tre nye udsendelser.

source_text: Already reporting in English and Japanese, the global organization is launching Spanish, Italian, and Korean-language programs, for television, the web, and mobile devices.
target_text: Den globale organisation sender allerede rapporter på engelsk og japansk og lancerer programmer på spansk, italiensk og koreansk til fjernsyn, internettet og mobile enheder.

source_text: "Luckily nothing happened to me, but I saw a macabre scene, as people tried to break windows in order to get out.
target_text: Heldigvis skete der ikke noget med mig, men jeg så et grusomt syn, hvor folk prøvede at bryde vinduer for at komme ud.

source_text: People were hitting the panes with chairs, but the windows were unbreakable.
target_text: Folk ramte panele med stoler, men vinduerne var ubrydelige.

source_text: One of the panes finally broke, and they started to get out by the window," said survivor Franciszek Kowal.
target_text: En af panerne brød til sidst, og de begyndte at komme ud ved vinduet, "sagde overlevende Franciszek Kowal.

source_text: Stars give off light and heat because of the energy made when hydrogen atoms are merged (or fused) together to form heavier elements.
target_text: Stjerner udsender lys og varme på grund af den energi, der opstår, når hydrogenatomer føjes (eller smeltet) sammen til at danne tungere elementer.

source_text: Scientists are working to create a reactor that can make energy in the same way.
target_text: Forskere arbejder på at skabe en reaktor der kan producere energi på samme måde.

source_text: This, however, is a very hard problem to solve and will take many years before we see useful fusion reactors built.
target_text: Dette er imidlertid et meget vanskeligt problem at løse, og det vil tage mange år, før vi ser nyttige fusionsreaktorer bygget.

source_text: The steel needle floats on top of the water because of surface tension.
target_text: Stålnålen flyver over vandet på grund af overfladenspænding.

source_text: Surface tension happens because the water molecules at the surface of the water are strongly attracted to each other more than they are to the air molecules above them.
target_text: Overfladenspænding opstår fordi vandmolekylerne på vandets overflade er stærkt tiltrukket af hinanden mere end de er til luftmolekylerne over dem.

source_text: The water molecules make an invisible skin on the water’s surface that allows things like the needle to float on top of the water.
target_text: Vandmolekylerne skaber en usynlig hud på vandets overflade, som gør det muligt for ting som nålen at flyde over vandet.

source_text: The blade on a modern ice skate has a double edge with a concave hollow between them. The two edges allow for a better grasp of the ice, even when tilted.
target_text: Bladeet på et moderne isskate har en dobbelt kant med en konkav hul mellem dem. De to kanter giver en bedre greb af isen, selv når den er henhøjlet.

source_text: Because the bottom of the blade is slightly curved, as the blade tilts to one side or the other, the edge which is in contact with the ice also curves.
target_text: Fordi bladesinden er lidt kurvet, når bladesiden hældes til den ene side eller den anden, er kanten, der er i kontakt med isen, også kurvet.

source_text: This causes the skater to turn. If the skates tilt to the right, the skater turns right, if the skates tilt to the left, the skater turns left.
target_text: Hvis skaterne hænger til højre, hænger skaterne til højre, hvis skaterne hænger til venstre, hænger skaterne til venstre.

source_text: To return to their previous energy level, they must get rid of the extra energy they got from the light.
target_text: For at vende tilbage til deres tidligere energiniveau, må de slippe af med den ekstra energi de fik fra lyset.

source_text: They do this by emitting a tiny particle of light called a "photon".
target_text: De gør dette ved at udsende en lille lyspartikel kaldet et "foton".

source_text: Scientists call this process "stimulated emission of radiation" because the atoms are stimulated by the bright light, causing the emission of a photon of light, and light is a type of radiation.
target_text: Forskere kalder denne proces "stimuleret udsendelse af stråling" fordi atomerne stimuleres af det skarpe lys, hvilket forårsager udsendelse af et lysfoton, og lys er en form for stråling.

source_text: The next picture shows the atoms emitting photons. Of course, in reality photons are a lot smaller than those in the picture.
target_text: Det næste billede viser atomer, der udsender fotoner. I virkeligheden er fotoner selvfølgelig meget mindre end dem i billedet.

source_text: Photons are even smaller than the stuff that makes up atoms!
target_text: Fotoner er endnu mindre end det stof der udgør atomer!

source_text: After hundreds of hours of operation the filament in the bulb eventually burns out and the light bulb no longer works.
target_text: Efter hundredvis af timers drift brænder ledningen i pæren til sidst ud, og pæren virker ikke længere.

source_text: The light bulb then needs replacing. It is necessary to be careful in replacing the light bulb.
target_text: Det er derfor nødvendigt at være forsigtig med at udskifte glødelampen.

source_text: First, the switch for the light fixture needs to be turned off or the cable disconnected.
target_text: For det første er det nødvendigt at slukke for lyset eller afbryde kablen.

source_text: This is because electricity flowing into the socket where the metallic part of bulb sits can give you a severe electric shock if you touch the inside of the socket or the metal base of the bulb while it is still partly in the socket.
target_text: Dette skyldes, at elektricitet, der strømmer ind i socketet, hvor den metalliske del af pærer sidder, kan give dig et alvorligt elektrisk chok, hvis du rører indvendigt i socketet eller metalbasen af pæren, mens den stadig er delvis i socketet.

source_text: The major organ of the circulatory system is the heart, which pumps the blood.
target_text: Det vigtigste organ i blodcirkulationen er hjertet, som pumper blodet.

source_text: Blood goes away from the heart in tubes called arteries and comes back to the heart in tubes called veins. The smallest tubes are called capillaries.
target_text: Blodet forsvinder fra hjertet i rør kaldet arterier og kommer tilbage til hjertet i rør kaldet vener.

source_text: A triceratops' teeth would have been able to crush not only leaves but even very tough branches and roots.
target_text: En triceratops tænder ville have været i stand til at knuse ikke kun blade, men også meget hårde grene og rødder.

source_text: Some scientists think Triceratops ate cycads, which are a type of plant that was common in the Cretaceous.
target_text: Nogle forskere tror Triceratops spiste cykader, som er en type plante der var almindelig i kredstiden.

source_text: These plants look like a small palm tree with a crown of sharp, spiky leaves.
target_text: Disse planter ligner et lille palmbræ med en krone af skarpe, pikke blade.

source_text: A Triceratops could have used its strong beak to strip off the leaves before eating the trunk.
target_text: En Triceratops kunne have brugt sin stærke pik til at fjerne bladene før de spiste stammen.

source_text: Other scientists argue that these plants are very poisonous so it is unlikely that any dinosaur ate them, even though today the sloth and other animals like the parrot (a descendant of the dinosaurs) can eat poisonous leaves or fruit.
target_text: Andre forskere hævder, at disse planter er meget giftige, så det er usandsynligt, at nogen dinosaurer spiste dem, selv om sløv og andre dyr som papegiggen (en efterkommer af dinosaurerne) i dag kan spise giftige blade eller frugt.

source_text: How would Io's gravity pull on me? If you stood on the surface of Io, you would weigh less than you do on Earth.
target_text: Hvis du stod på Io's overflade, ville du veje mindre end på Jorden.

source_text: A person who weighs 200 pounds (90kg) on Earth would weigh about 36 pounds (16kg) on Io. So the gravity, of course, pulls less on you.
target_text: En person, der vejer 90 kg på Jorden, ville veje omkring 16 kg på Io. Så tyngdekraften trækker naturligvis mindre på dig.

source_text: The Sun doesn't have a crust like the Earth that you can stand on. The whole Sun is made out of gases, fire, and plasma.
target_text: Solen har ikke en jordskorpe, som man kan stå på. Hele solen er lavet af gasser, ild og plasma.

source_text: The gas becomes thinner as you go farther from the center of the Sun.
target_text: Gassen bliver tyndere efterhånden som man går længere væk fra solens centrum.

source_text: The outer-part we see when we look at the Sun is called the photosphere, which means "ball of light".
target_text: Den ydre del vi ser når vi kigger på solen kaldes fotosfæren, hvilket betyder "lyskugle".

source_text: About three thousand years later, in 1610, Italian astronomer Galileo Galilei used a telescope to observe that Venus has phases, just as the moon does.
target_text: Omkring tre tusind år senere, i 1610, brugte den italienske astronom Galileo Galilei et teleskop til at observere at Venus har faser ligesom månen.

source_text: Phases happen because only the side of Venus (or of the Moon) facing the Sun is lighted. The phases of Venus supported the theory of Copernicus that the planets go around the Sun.
target_text: Venus' faser understøttede Copernicus' teori om at planeterne går rundt om solen.

source_text: Then, a few years later in 1639, an English astronomer named Jeremiah Horrocks observed a transit of Venus.
target_text: Nogle år senere, i 1639, observerede en engelsk astronom ved navn Jeremiah Horrocks en transit af Venus.

source_text: England had experienced a long period of peace after the reconquest of the Danelaw.
target_text: England havde oplevet en lang periode med fred efter at have generobret Danelaw.

source_text: However in 991 Ethelred was faced with a Viking fleet larger than any since Guthrum's a century earlier.
target_text: Men i 991 blev Ethelred konfronteret med en vikingflåde større end nogen siden Guthrums et århundrede tidligere.

source_text: This fleet was led by Olaf Trygvasson, a Norwegian with ambitions to reclaim his country from Danish domination.
target_text: Denne flåde blev ledet af Olaf Trygvasson, en norsk med ambitioner om at genvinde sit land fra dansk dominans.

source_text: After initial military setbacks, Ethelred was able to agree to terms with Olaf, who returned to Norway to try to gain his kingdom with mixed success.
target_text: Efter de første militære nederlag, Ethelred var i stand til at acceptere aftaler med Olaf, som vendte tilbage til Norge for at forsøge at få sit kongerige med blandet succes.

source_text: Hangeul is the only purposely invented alphabet in popular daily use. The alphabet was invented in 1444 during the reign of King Sejong (1418 – 1450).
target_text: Hangeul er det eneste bevidst opfundede alfabet i almindelig daglig brug. alfabetet blev opfundet i 1444 under kong Sejongs regeringstid (1418  1450).

source_text: King Sejong was the fourth king of the Joseon Dynasty and is one of the most highly regarded.
target_text: Kong Sejong var den fjerde konge i Joseon-dynastiet og er en af de mest højt respekterede.

source_text: He originally named the Hangeul alphabet Hunmin Jeongeum, which means "the correct sounds for the instruction of the people".
target_text: Han kaldte oprindeligt Hangeul-alfabetet Hunmin Jeongeum, hvilket betyder "de korrekte lyde til at undervise folket".

source_text: There are many theories to how Sanskrit came into existence. One of them is about an Aryan migration from the west into India who brought their language with them.
target_text: Der er mange teorier om, hvordan sanskrit kom til eksistens. En af dem handler om en ariansk migration fra vesten til Indien, der bragte deres sprog med sig.

source_text: Sanskrit is an ancient language and is comparable to the Latin language spoken in Europe.
target_text: Sanskrit er et gammelt sprog og kan sammenlignes med det latinske sprog der tales i Europa.

source_text: The earliest known book in the world was written in Sanskrit. After the compilation of Upanishads, Sanskrit just faded due to hierarchy.
target_text: Den tidligste kendte bog i verden blev skrevet på sanskrit.

source_text: Sanskrit is a very complex and rich language, which has served to be the source for many modern Indian languages, just like Latin is the source for European languages like French and Spanish.
target_text: Sanskrit er et meget komplekst og rigt sprog, som har været kilden til mange moderne indiske sprog, ligesom latin er kilden til europæiske sprog som fransk og spansk.

source_text: With the battle for France over, Germany began to get ready to invade the island of Britain.
target_text: Da kampen for Frankrig var overstået, begyndte Tyskland at forberede sig på at invadere øen Storbritannien.

source_text: Germany code-named the attack “Operation Sealion”. Most of the British Army's heavy weapons and supplies had been lost when it evacuated from Dunkirk, so the army was fairly weak.
target_text: Tyskland kaldte angrebet "Operation Sealion". De fleste af den britiske hærs tunge våben og forsyninger var gået tabt, da den evakuerede fra Dunkirk, så hæren var ret svag.

source_text: But the Royal Navy was still much stronger than the German Navy (“Kriegsmarine”) and could have destroyed any invasion fleet sent across the English Channel.
target_text: Men Royal Navy var stadig meget stærkere end den tyske flåde (Kriegsmarine) og kunne have ødelagt enhver invasion flåde sendt over den engelske kanal.

source_text: However, very few Royal Navy ships were based near the likely invasion routes as the admirals were afraid they would be sunk by German air attack.
target_text: Men meget få Royal Navy skibe var baseret nær de sandsynlige invasionsruter, da admiralerne var bange for at de ville blive synket af tysk luftangreb.

source_text: Let's start with an explanation about Italy's plans. Italy was mainly the "little brother" of Germany and Japan.
target_text: Lad os begynde med en forklaring på Italiens planer. Italien var hovedsageligt Tysklands og Japans "småbror".

source_text: It had a weaker army and a weaker navy, although they had just built four new ships right before the beginning of the war.
target_text: Den havde en svagere hær og en svagere flåde, selv om de lige havde bygget fire nye skibe lige før krigen begyndte.

source_text: Italy's main goals were African countries. To capture those countries, they would need to have a troop launching pad, so as troops could sail across the Mediterranean Sea and invade Africa.
target_text: For at besejre disse lande skulle Italien have brug for en troppeafladning, så tropperne kunne sejle over Middelhavet og invadere Afrika.

source_text: For that, they had to get rid of British bases and ships in Egypt. Besides those actions, Italy's battleships were not supposed to do anything else.
target_text: For at opnå dette var de nødt til at slippe af med de britiske baser og skibe i Egypten.

source_text: Now for Japan. Japan was an island country, just like Britain.
target_text: Japan var et øland, ligesom Storbritannien.

source_text: Submarines are ships designed to travel underwater, and remain there for an extended amount of time.
target_text: U-både er skibe designet til at rejse under vandet, og forbliver der i en længere periode.

source_text: Submarines were used in World War I and World War II. Back then they were very slow and had a very limited shooting range.
target_text: U-både blev brugt i Første og Anden Verdenskrig.

source_text: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen.
target_text: I begyndelsen af krigen rejste de for det meste over havet, men da radarerne begyndte at udvikle sig og blive mere præcise, blev ubåderne tvunget til at gå under vandet for at undgå at blive set.

source_text: German submarines were called U-Boats. The Germans were very good at navigating and operating their submarines.
target_text: Tyske ubåde blev kaldt U-både. Tyskerne var meget gode til at navigere og betjene deres ubåde.

source_text: Because of their success with submarines, after the war Germans aren't trusted to have many of them.
target_text: På grund af deres succes med ubåde efter krigen har tyskerne ikke tillid til at have mange af dem.

source_text: Yes! King Tutankhamun, sometimes referred to as "King Tut" or "The Boy King", is one of the most well known ancient Egyptian kings in modern times.
target_text: Kong Tutankhamon, som nogle gange kaldes "kong Tut" eller "den unge konge", er en af de mest kendte gamle egyptiske konger i moderne tid.

source_text: Interestingly, he was not considered to be very important in ancient times and was not recorded on most ancient king lists.
target_text: Interessant nok blev han ikke betragtet som meget vigtig i antikken og blev ikke opført på de fleste gamle kongeliste.

source_text: However, the discovery of his tomb in 1922 made him a celebrity. While many tombs of the past were robbed, this tomb was left virtually undisturbed.
target_text: Men efter at hans grav blev opdaget i 1922 blev han en berømt person.

source_text: Most of the items buried with Tutankhamun have been well preserved, including thousands of artefacts made from precious metals and rare stones.
target_text: De fleste af de ting der er begravet sammen med Tutankhamun er bevaret godt, herunder tusindvis af artefakter lavet af ædelmetaller og sjældne sten.

source_text: The invention of spoke wheels made Assyrian chariots lighter, faster, and better prepared to outrun soldiers and other chariots.
target_text: Ved opfindelsen af hjul gjorde de assyriske vogne lettere, hurtigere og bedre forberedt på at løbe foran soldater og andre vogne.

source_text: Arrows from their deadly crossbows could penetrate the armor of rival soldiers. About 1000 B.C., the Assyrians introduced the first cavalry.
target_text: Pilen fra deres dødelige båge kunne trænge ind i rivaliserende soldaters rustning.

source_text: A cavalry is an army that fights on horseback. The saddle had not yet been invented, so the Assyrian cavalry fought on the bare backs of their horses.
target_text: En hestevogn er en hær der kæmper på heste. Sædet var endnu ikke opfundet, så den assyriske hestevogn kæmpede bare på deres heste.

source_text: We know many Greek politicians, scientists, and artists. Possibly the most known person of this culture is Homer, the legendary blind poet, who composed two masterpieces of Greek literature: the poems Iliad and Odyssey.
target_text: Vi kender mange græske politikere, videnskabsmænd og kunstnere, og måske den mest kendte person i denne kultur er Homer, den legendariske blinde digter, der komponerede to mesterværker i græsk litteratur: digterne Iliad og Odyssey.

source_text: Sophocles and Aristophanes are still popular playwrights and their plays are considered to be among the greatest works of world literature.
target_text: Sophocles og Aristophanes er stadig populære dramatikere, og deres skuespil anses for at være blandt verdens største værker.

source_text: Another famous Greek is a mathematician Pythagoras, mostly known for his famous theorem about relations of the sides of right triangles.
target_text: En anden berømt græker er en matematiker Pythagoras, mest kendt for sit berømte teoreme om forholdet mellem siderne af retre trekanter.

source_text: There are varying estimates for how many people speak Hindi. It is estimated to be between the second and fourth most commonly spoken language in the world.
target_text: Der er forskellige skøn for hvor mange mennesker der taler hindi. Det anslås at være mellem det andet og fjerde mest talte sprog i verden.

source_text: The number of native speakers varies depending on whether or not very closely related dialects are counted.
target_text: Antallet af indfødte talere varierer afhængigt af, om der tælles meget nært beslægtede dialekter.

source_text: Estimates range from 340 million to 500 million speakers, and as many as 800 million people can understand the language.
target_text: Man anslår at der er mellem 340 millioner og 500 millioner talere, og at op til 800 millioner mennesker kan forstå sproget.

source_text: Hindi and Urdu are similar in vocabulary but different in script; in everyday conversations, speakers of both languages can usually understand each other.
target_text: Hindi og Urdu er ligegyldige i ordforråd, men forskellige i skrift; i daglig samtale, kan talere af begge sprog normalt forstå hinanden.

source_text: Around the 15th century, northern Estonia was under great cultural influence of Germany.
target_text: Omkring det 15. århundrede var det nordlige Estland under stor kulturel indflydelse fra Tyskland.

source_text: Some German monks wanted to bring God closer to the native people, so they invented the Estonian literal language.
target_text: Nogle tyske munke ønskede at bringe Gud tættere på de indfødte, så de opfandt det estiske bogstavelige sprog.

source_text: It was based on the German alphabet and one character "Õ/õ" was added.
target_text: Det var baseret på det tyske alfabet og ét tegn "Õ/õ" blev tilføjet.

source_text: As time passed, many words that were borrowed from German coalesced. This was the beginning of enlightenment.
target_text: Efterhånden som tiden gik, blev mange ord, der låntes fra tysk, sammensat.

source_text: Traditionally, the heir to the throne would go straight into the military after finishing school.
target_text: Traditionelt gik tronsæden direkte ind i militæret efter at have afsluttet skolen.

source_text: However, Charles went to university at Trinity College, Cambridge where he studied Anthropology and Archaeology, and later History, earning a 2:2 (a lower second class degree).
target_text: Men Charles gik på universitetet på Trinity College i Cambridge, hvor han studerede antropologi og arkæologi, og senere historie, og tjente en 2: 2 (en lavere anden klasse grad).

source_text: Charles was the first member of the British Royal Family to be awarded a degree.
target_text: Charles var det første medlem af den britiske kongelige familie til at blive tildelt en grad.

source_text: European Turkey (eastern Thrace or Rumelia in the Balkan peninsula) includes 3% of the country.
target_text: Den europæiske Tyrkiet (østlige Thrakien eller Rumelia på Balkanhalvøen) omfatter 3% af landet.

source_text: The territory of Turkey is more than 1,600 kilometres (1,000 mi) long and 800 km (500 mi) wide, with a roughly rectangular shape.
target_text: Tyrkiets territorium er mere end 1.600 kilometer lang og 800 km bred, med en omtrent rektangulær form.

source_text: Turkey's area, including lakes, occupies 783,562 square kilometres (300,948 sq mi), of which 755,688 square kilometres (291,773 sq mi) are in south west Asia and 23,764 square kilometres (9,174 sq mi) in Europe.
target_text: Tyrkiets areal, herunder søer, besætter 783.562 kvadratkilometer (300.948 kvadrat miles), hvoraf 755.688 kvadratkilometer (291.773 kvadrat miles) er i sydvestlige Asien og 23.764 kvadratkilometer (9.174 kvadrat miles) i Europa.

source_text: Turkey's area makes it the world's 37th-largest country, and is about the size of Metropolitan France and the United Kingdom combined.
target_text: Tyrkiets areal gør det til verdens 37. største land, og er omkring størrelsen på Metropolitan Frankrig og Det Forenede Kongerige tilsammen.

source_text: Turkey is encircled by seas on three sides: the Aegean Sea to the west, the Black Sea to the north and the Mediterranean Sea to the south.
target_text: Tyrkiet er omringet af hav på tre sider: Ægeiske Hav i vest, Sorte Hav i nord og Middelhavet i syd.

source_text: Luxembourg has a long history but its independence dates from 1839.
target_text: Luxembourg har en lang historie, men dets uafhængighed stammer fra 1839.

source_text: Present-day parts of Belgium were part of Luxembourg in the past but became Belgian after the 1830s Belgian Revolution.
target_text: De nuværende dele af Belgien var tidligere en del af Luxembourg, men blev belgiske efter den belgiske revolution i 1830'erne.

source_text: Luxembourg has always tried to remain a neutral country but it was occupied in both World War I and World War II by Germany.
target_text: Luxembourg har altid forsøgt at forblive et neutralt land, men det blev besat i både Første og Anden Verdenskrig af Tyskland.

source_text: In 1957 Luxembourg became a founding member of the organization which is today known as the European Union.
target_text: I 1957 blev Luxembourg grundlægger af den organisation, der i dag er kendt som Den Europæiske Union.

source_text: The Drukgyal Dzong is a ruined fortress and Buddhist monastery in the upper part of the Paro District (in Phondey Village).
target_text: Drukgyal Dzong er en ruineret fæstning og buddhistisk kloster i den øvre del af Paro District (i Phondey Village).

source_text: It is said that in 1649, Zhabdrung Ngawang Namgyel created the fortress to commemorate his victory against the Tibetan-Mongol forces.
target_text: Det siges, at Zhabdrung Ngawang Namgyel i 1649 oprettede fæstningen til at mindes sin sejr mod de tibetansk-mongole styrker.

source_text: In 1951, a fire caused for only some of the relics of the Drukgyal Dzong to remain, such as the image of Zhabdrung Ngawang Namgyal.
target_text: I 1951 forårsagede en brand at kun nogle af relikvierne af Drukgyal Dzong blev tilbage, såsom billedet af Zhabdrung Ngawang Namgyal.

source_text: After the fire, the fortress was preserved and protected, remaining to be one of Bhutan's most sensational attractions.
target_text: Efter branden blev fæstningen bevaret og beskyttet og blev en af Bhutans mest sensationelle attraktioner.

source_text: During the 18th century Cambodia found itself squeezed between two powerful neighbors, Thailand and Vietnam.
target_text: I det 18. århundrede var Kambodsja klemt mellem to magtfulde naboer, Thailand og Vietnam.

source_text: The Thais invaded Cambodia several times in the 18th century and in 1772 they destroyed Phnom Phen.
target_text: Thailænderne invaderede Kambodsja flere gange i det 18. århundrede, og i 1772 ødelagde de Phnom Phen.

source_text: In the last years of the 18th century the Vietnamese also invaded Cambodia.
target_text: I de sidste år af det 18. århundrede invaderede vietnameserne også Kambodsja.

source_text: Eighteen percent of Venezuelans are unemployed, and most of those who are employed work in the informal economy.
target_text: 18 procent af venezuelerne er arbejdsløse, og de fleste af dem der er beskæftiget arbejder i den uformelle økonomi.

source_text: Two thirds of Venezuelans who work do so in the service sector, nearly a quarter work in industry and a fifth work in agriculture.
target_text: To tredjedele af de venezuelanere, der arbejder, arbejder i tjenesteydelsessektoren, næsten en fjerdedel arbejder i industrien og en femtedel i landbruget.

source_text: An important industry for Venezuelans is oil, where the country is a net exporter, even though only one percent work in the oil industry.
target_text: En vigtig branche for venezuelanerne er olie, hvor landet er en nettoeksporter, selvom kun én procent arbejder i olieindustrien.

source_text: Early in the nation's independence, Singapore Botanic Gardens' expertise helped to transform the island into a tropical Garden City.
target_text: I begyndelsen af landets uafhængighed hjalp Singapore Botanic Gardens ekspertise til at forvandle øen til en tropisk Garden City.

source_text: In 1981, Vanda Miss Joaquim, an orchid hybrid, was chosen as the nation's national flower.
target_text: I 1981 blev Vanda Miss Joaquim, en orkidehybrid, valgt som landets nationale blomst.

source_text: Every year around October nearly 1.5 million herbivores travel towards the southern plains, crossing the Mara River, from the northern hills for the rains.
target_text: Hvert år omkring oktober rejser næsten 1,5 millioner planteædende til de sydlige sletter, krydser Marafloden, fra de nordlige bakker for regnen.

source_text: And then back to the north through the west, once again crossing the Mara river, after the rains in around April.
target_text: Og så tilbage mod nord gennem vest, igen krydser Marafloden, efter regnen i omkring april.

source_text: The Serengeti region contains the Serengeti National Park, the Ngorongoro Conservation Area and Maswa Game Reserve in Tanzania and the Maasai Mara National Reserve in Kenya.
target_text: Serengeti-regionen indeholder Serengeti National Park, Ngorongoro Conservation Area og Maswa Game Reserve i Tanzania og Maasai Mara National Reserve i Kenya.

source_text: Learning to create interactive media requires conventional and traditional skills, as well as tools mastered in interactive classes (storyboarding, audio and video editing, story telling, etc.)
target_text: At lære at skabe interaktive medier kræver konventionelle og traditionelle færdigheder samt værktøjer, der er dygtige i interaktive klasser (storyboarding, lyd- og videoredigering, fortælling osv.).

source_text: Interactive design requires that you re-assess your assumptions about media production and learn to think in a non-linear ways.
target_text: Interaktivt design kræver, at du revurderer dine antagelser om medieproduktion og lærer at tænke på en ikke-lineær måde.

source_text: Interactive design requires that components of a project connect to each other, but also make sense as a separate entity.
target_text: Interaktiv design kræver, at komponenterne i et projekt forbinder hinanden, men også giver mening som en separat enhed.

source_text: The disadvantage of zoom lenses is that the focal complexity and number of lens elements required to achieve a range of focal lengths is much greater than for prime lenses.
target_text: Fordelen ved zoomlinser er, at fokuskompleksiteten og antallet af objektivelementer, der kræves for at opnå en række fokuslængder, er meget større end for hovedlinser.

source_text: This is becoming less of an issue as lens manufacturers achieve higher standards in lens production.
target_text: Dette bliver mindre af et problem, da linsfabrikanterne når højere standarder i linsproduktionen.

source_text: This has allowed zoom lenses to produce pictures of a quality comparable to that achieved by lenses with fixed focal length.
target_text: Dette har gjort det muligt for zoomlinser at producere billeder af en kvalitet sammenlignelig med den opnået ved linser med fast fokusvidde.

source_text: Another disadvantage of zoom lenses is that the maximum aperture (the speed) of the lens is usually lower.
target_text: En anden ulempe ved zoomlinser er, at den maksimale åbning (hastigheden) af linsen normalt er lavere.

source_text: This makes inexpensive zoom lenses hard to use in low-light conditions without a flash.
target_text: Dette gør billige zoomlinser vanskelige at bruge under lave lysforhold uden en blink.

source_text: One of the most common problems when trying to convert a movie to DVD format is the overscan.
target_text: Et af de mest almindelige problemer, når man forsøger at konvertere en film til DVD-format, er overskanningen.

source_text: Most televisions are made in a way to please the general public.
target_text: De fleste fjernsyn er lavet på en måde, der glæder offentligheden.

source_text: For that reason, everything you see on the TV had the borders cut, top, bottom and sides.
target_text: Af den grund har alt, hvad du ser på tv, haft grænserne skåret, øverst, nederst og siderne.

source_text: This is made to ensure that the image covers the whole screen. That is called overscan.
target_text: Dette gøres for at sikre, at billedet dækker hele skærmen.

source_text: Unfortunately, when you make a DVD, it's borders will most likely be cut too, and if the video had subtitles too close to the bottom, they won't be fully shown.
target_text: Desværre, når du laver en DVD, vil dens grænser sandsynligvis også blive skåret, og hvis videoen havde undertekster for tæt på bunden, vil de ikke blive vist fuldt ud.

source_text: The traditional medieval castle has long inspired the imagination, conjuring up images of jousts, banquets and Arthurian chivalry.
target_text: Det traditionelle middelaldersk slott har længe inspireret fantasien, idet det fremkalder billeder af jousts, banketter og arthurisk ridderlighed.

source_text: Even standing amidst thousand year-old ruins it is easy to bring to mind the sounds and smells of battles long gone, to almost hear the clatter of hooves on the cobbles and to smell the fear rising from the dungeon pits.
target_text: Selv når man står midt i et tusind år gamle ruiner, kan man let huske lyden og lugten af slag, der er gået længe siden, næsten høre klumringen af hofter på stenstenene og lugte frygten fra dungeongrøderne.

source_text: But is our imagination based on reality? Why were castles built in the first place? How were they designed and built?
target_text: Men er vores fantasi baseret på virkeligheden? Hvorfor blev slotte bygget i første omgang? Hvordan blev de designet og bygget?

source_text: Typical for the period, Kirby Muxloe Castle is more of a fortified house than a true castle.
target_text: Typisk for perioden er Kirby Muxloe Castle mere et befæstet hus end et rigtigt slot.

source_text: Its large glazed windows and thin walls would not have been able to resist a determined attack for long.
target_text: Dens store glasrede vinduer og tynde vægge ville ikke have været i stand til at modstå et bestemt angreb i lang tid.

source_text: In the 1480s, when its construction was begun by Lord Hastings, the country was relatively peaceful and defense was only required against small bands of roving marauders.
target_text: I 1480'erne, da bygningen blev påbegyndt af Lord Hastings, var landet relativt fredeligt, og forsvaret var kun nødvendigt mod små bander vandrende røvere.

source_text: The balance of power was a system in which European nations sought to maintain the national sovereignty of all European states.
target_text: Magtsbalancen var et system, hvor de europæiske nationer søgte at opretholde alle europæiske staters nationale suverænitet.

source_text: The concept was that all European nations had to seek to prevent one nation from becoming powerful, and thus national governments often changed their alliances in order to maintain the balance.
target_text: Begrebet var, at alle europæiske nationer skulle forsøge at forhindre en nation i at blive magtfuld, og derfor ændrede nationale regeringer ofte deres alliancer for at opretholde balancen.

source_text: The War of Spanish Succession marked the first war whose central issue was the balance of power.
target_text: Den spanske efterfølgelseskrig markerede den første krig, hvis centrale spørgsmål var magtbalancen.

source_text: This marked an important change, as European powers would no longer have the pretext of being religious wars. Thus, the Thirty Years' War would be the last war to be labeled a religious war.
target_text: Dette markerede en vigtig ændring, da de europæiske magter ikke længere ville have forskyldningen for at være religiøse krige.

source_text: The temple of Artemis at Ephesus was destroyed on July 21, 356 BCE in an act of arson committed by Herostratus.
target_text: Artemis templet i Efesus blev ødelagt den 21. juli 356 f.Kr. i en brænding begået af Herostratus.

source_text: According to the story, his motivation was fame at any cost. The Ephesians, outraged, announced that Herostratus' name never be recorded.
target_text: Ifølge historien var hans motivation berømmelse til enhver pris.

source_text: The Greek historian Strabo later noted the name, which is how we know today. The temple was destroyed on the same night that Alexander the Great was born.
target_text: Den græske historiker Strabo skrev senere at templet blev ødelagt samme nat som Alexander den Store blev født.

source_text: Alexander, as king, offered to pay to rebuild the temple, but his offer was denied. Later, after Alexander died, the temple was rebuilt in 323 BCE.
target_text: Alexander, som konge, tilbød at betale for at genopbygge templet, men hans tilbud blev afvist. Senere, efter Alexander døde, blev templet genopbygget i 323 f.Kr.

source_text: Make sure your hand is as relaxed as possible while still hitting all the notes correctly - also try not to make much extraneous motion with your fingers.
target_text: Sørg for at din hånd er så afslappet som muligt mens du stadig trykker på alle noterne korrekt - og prøv også ikke at gøre så mange fremmedbevægelser med dine fingre.

source_text: This way, you will tire yourself out as little as possible. Remember there's no need to hit the keys with a lot of force for extra volume like on the piano.
target_text: På den måde vil du trætte dig så lidt som muligt. Husk, at du ikke behøver at trykke på tastaturerne med så meget kraft for ekstra lyd som på klaveret.

source_text: On the accordion, to get extra volume, you use the bellows with more pressure or speed.
target_text: På akordeonerne, for at få ekstra volumen, bruger man blæsen med mere tryk eller hastighed.

source_text: Mysticism is the pursuit of communion with, identity with, or conscious awareness of an ultimate reality, divinity, spiritual truth, or God.
target_text: Mystik er stræben efter fællesskab med, identitet med eller bevidst bevidst bevidsthed om en ultimativ virkelighed, guddommelighed, åndelig sandhed eller Gud.

source_text: The believer seeks a direct experience, intuition, or insight into divine reality/the deity or dieties.
target_text: Den troende søger direkte erfaring, intuition eller indsigt i den guddommelige virkelighed/guddommen eller dieter.

source_text: Followers pursue certain ways of living, or practices that are intended to nurture those experiences.
target_text: Efterfølgere følger visse livsstiler eller praksis der er beregnet til at opdyrke disse oplevelser.

source_text: Mysticism can be distinguished from other forms of religious belief and worship by its emphasis on the direct personal experience of a unique state of consciousness, particularly those of a peaceful, insightful, blissful, or even ecstatic character.
target_text: Mystik kan adskilles fra andre former for religiøs tro og tilbedelse ved at den lægger vægt på den direkte personlige oplevelse af en unik bevidsthedstilstand, især den af en fredelig, indsigtsfuld, lykkelig eller endog ekstatisk karakter.

source_text: Sikhism is a religion from the Indian sub-continent. It originated in the Punjab region during the 15th century from a sectarian split within the Hindu tradition.
target_text: Sikhisme er en religion fra det indiske subkontinent.

source_text: Sikhs consider their faith to be a separate religion from Hinduism though they acknowledge its Hindu roots and traditions.
target_text: Sikher betragter deres tro som en særskilt religion fra hinduismen, selv om de anerkender dens hinduistiske rødder og traditioner.

source_text: Sikhs call their religion Gurmat, which is Punjabi for "way of the guru". The guru is a fundamental aspect of all Indian religions but in Sikhism has taken on an importance that forms the core of Sikh beliefs.
target_text: Sikhs kalder deres religion Gurmat, som er Punjabi for "gurus vej". Guruen er et grundlæggende aspekt af alle indiske religioner, men i Sikhisme har taget en betydning, der udgør kernen i Sikh overbevisninger.

source_text: The religion was founded in the 15th century by Guru Nanak (1469–1539). There followed in succession a further nine gurus.
target_text: Religionen blev grundlagt i det 15. århundrede af Guru Nanak (14691539).

source_text: However, in June 1956, Krushchev's promises were put to the test when riots in Poland, where workers were protesting against food shortages and wage cuts, turned into a general protest against Communism.
target_text: Men i juni 1956 blev Krusjcevs løfter sat på prøve da urolighederne i Polen, hvor arbejderne protesterede mod mangel på mad og lønsnedskæringer, blev til en generel protest mod kommunismen.

source_text: Although in the end, Krushchev sent in tanks to restore order, he did give way to some economic demands and agreed to appoint the popular Wladyslaw Gomulka as the new prime minister.
target_text: Selv om Krusjtsjov i sidste ende sendte i kampvogne for at genoprette orden, gav han plads til nogle økonomiske krav og accepterede at udpege den populære Wladyslaw Gomulka som ny premierminister.

source_text: The Indus Valley Civilization was a Bronze Age civilisation in the northwest Indian subcontinent encompassing most of modern-day Pakistan and some regions in northwest India and northeast Afghanistan.
target_text: Indus-dalen civilisation var en bronzealder civilisation i det nordvestlige indiske subkontinent, der omfattede det meste af nutidens Pakistan og nogle regioner i det nordvestlige Indien og det nordøstlige Afghanistan.

source_text: The civilisation flourished in the basins of the Indus River wherefore it derives its name.
target_text: Civilisationen blomstrede i Indusflodens bassiner, og derfor har den fået sit navn.

source_text: Although some scholars speculate that since the civilisation also existed in the basins of the now dried up Sarasvati River, it should be aptly called the Indus-Sarasvati Civilization, while some call it the Harappan Civilization after Harappa, the first of its sites to be excavated in the 1920s.
target_text: Selv om nogle forskere spekulerer på, at siden civilisationen også eksisterede i bassinerne af den nu tørrede Sarasvati-flod, bør den med rette kaldes Indus-Sarasvati-civilisationen, mens nogle kalder den Harappan-civilisationen efter Harappa, den første af sine steder at blive udgravet i 1920'erne.

source_text: The militaristic nature of the Roman empire aided in the development of medical advances.
target_text: Det romerske imperiums militarisme bidrog til udviklingen af medicinsk udvikling.

source_text: Doctors began to be recruited by Emperor Augustus and even formed the first Roman Medical Corps for use in the aftermath of battles.
target_text: Kejseren Augustus begyndte at rekruttere læger og dannede endda det første romerske medicinske korps til brug efter slagene.

source_text: Surgeons had knowledge of various sedatives including morphine from extracts of poppy seeds and scopolamine from herbane seeds.
target_text: Kirurger havde kendskab til forskellige beroligende midler, herunder morfin fra ekstrakter af malmfrø og scopolamin fra plantefrø.

source_text: They became proficient at amputation to save patients from gangrene as well as tourniquets and arterial clamps to stem blood flow.
target_text: De blev dygtige til at amputere patienter for at redde dem fra gangren, samt til at holde blodgennemstrømningen i stand.

source_text: Over multiple centuries, the Roman empire led to great gains in the field of medicine and formed much of the knowledge we know today.
target_text: I løbet af flere århundreder førte det romerske rige til store fremskridt inden for medicin og udgjorde en stor del af den viden vi kender i dag.

source_text: Pureland origami is origami with the restriction that only one fold may be done at a time, more complex folds like reverse folds are not allowed, and all folds have straightforward locations.
target_text: Pureland origami er origami med begrænsningen på, at kun én fold kan gøres ad gangen, mere komplekse fold som omvendte fold er ikke tilladt, og alle fold har enkle placeringer.

source_text: It was developed by John Smith in the 1970s to help inexperienced folders or those with limited motor skills.
target_text: Den blev udviklet af John Smith i 1970'erne for at hjælpe uerfarne mapper eller dem med begrænsede motoriske færdigheder.

source_text: Children develop an awareness of race and racial stereotypes quite young and these racial stereotypes affect behavior.
target_text: Børn udvikler en bevidsthed om race og racemæssige stereotyper ganske ung, og disse racemæssige stereotyper påvirker adfærd.

source_text: For instance, children who identify with a racial minority that is stereotyped as not doing well in school tend to not do well in school once they learn about the stereotype associated with their race.
target_text: For eksempel har børn, der identificerer sig med et etnisk mindretal, der er stereotyper som ikke gør godt i skolen, tendens til ikke at gøre godt i skolen, når de lærer om den stereotype der er forbundet med deres race.

source_text: MySpace is the third most popular website used in the United States and has 54 million profiles currently.
target_text: MySpace er det tredje mest populære websted i USA og har 54 millioner profiler i øjeblikket.

source_text: These websites have gotten a lot of attention, especially in the education setting.
target_text: Disse hjemmesider har fået stor opmærksomhed, især inden for uddannelse.

source_text: There are positive aspects to these websites, which include, being able to easily setup a class page which can include blogs, videos, photos, and other features.
target_text: Der er positive aspekter ved disse hjemmesider, som bl.a. at nemt kunne oprette en klasse side, der kan omfatte blogs, videoer, billeder og andre funktioner.

source_text: This page can easily be accessed by providing just one web address, which makes it easy to remember and easy to type in for students who may have trouble using the keyboard or with spelling.
target_text: Denne side er let at få adgang til ved at angive kun en webadresse, hvilket gør det nemt at huske og nemt at skrive ind for studerende, der måske har problemer med at bruge tastaturet eller med stavning.

source_text: It can be customized to make it easy to read and also with as much or little color as desired.
target_text: Det kan tilpasses til at gøre det nemt at læse og også med så meget eller lidt farve som ønsket.

source_text: Attention Deficit Disorder "is a neurological syndrome whose classic defining triad of symptoms including impulsivity, distractibility, and hyperactivity or excess energy".
target_text: Attention Deficit Disorder "er et neurologisk syndrom, hvis klassiske definerende triade af symptomer omfatter impulsivitet, distractibility og hyperactivity eller overflod af energi".

source_text: It is not a learning disability, it is a learning disorder; it "affects 3 to 5 percent of all children, perhaps as many as 2 million American children".
target_text: Det er ikke en læringsforstyrrelse, men en læringsforstyrrelse; den "berører 3 til 5 procent af alle børn, måske så mange som 2 millioner amerikanske børn".

source_text: Children with ADD have a hard time focusing on things like school work, but they can concentrate on things they enjoy doing like playing games or watching their favorite cartoons or writing sentences without punctuation.
target_text: Børn med ADHD har svært ved at fokusere på ting som skolearbejde, men de kan koncentrere sig om ting de nyder at gøre som at spille spil eller se deres yndlingsbilleder eller skrive sætninger uden punktur.

source_text: These children tend to get into a lot of trouble, because they "engage in risky behaviors, get into fights, and challenge authority" in order to stimulate their brain, since their brain can not be stimulated by normal methods.
target_text: Disse børn har en tendens til at komme i mange problemer, fordi de "begår risikable adfærd, kæmper og udfordrer myndighed" for at stimulere deres hjerne, da deres hjerne ikke kan stimuleres ved normale metoder.

source_text: ADD affects relationships with other peers because other children can not understand why they act the way that they do or why they spell they way they do or that their maturity level is different.
target_text: ADD påvirker forholdene med andre jævnaldrende fordi andre børn ikke kan forstå hvorfor de opfører sig på den måde de gør, eller hvorfor de skriver det på den måde de gør, eller at deres modenhed er anderledes.

source_text: As the ability to obtain knowledge and to learn changed in such a way as mentioned above the base rate at which knowledge was obtained changed.
target_text: Efterhånden som evnen til at opnå viden og at lære ændrede sig på en sådan måde, som nævnt ovenfor, ændrede basisraten, hvormed viden blev opnået.

source_text: The approach to obtaining information was different. No longer did pressure reside within individual recall, but the ability to recall text became more of a focus.
target_text: Det var ikke længere presset om at huske en person, men evnen til at huske tekst blev mere fokuseret.

source_text: In essence, the Renaissance made a significant change in the approach to learning and the dissemination of knowledge.
target_text: I det væsentlige gjorde renæssancen en væsentlig ændring i tilgangen til læring og videns udbredelse.

source_text: Unlike other primates, hominids no longer use their hands in locomotion or bearing weight or swinging through the trees.
target_text: I modsætning til andre primater bruger hominider ikke længere deres hænder til at bevæge sig eller bære vægt eller svinge gennem træerne.

source_text: The chimpanzee's hand and foot are similar in size and length, reflecting the hand's use for bearing weight in knuckle walking.
target_text: Chimpansens hænder og fødder er af samme størrelse og længde, hvilket afspejler håndens brug til at bære vægt i knoklet gang.

source_text: The human hand is shorter than the foot, with straighter phalanges.
target_text: Den menneskelige hånd er kortere end foden, med rettere phalanges.

source_text: Fossil hand bones two million to three million years old reveal this shift in specialization of the hand from locomotion to manipulation.
target_text: Fossile håndben, der er to til tre millioner år gamle, viser dette skift i specialisering af hånden fra bevægelse til manipulation.

source_text: Some people believe that experiencing many artificially induced lucid dreams often enough can be very exhausting.
target_text: Nogle mennesker mener at det kan være meget udmattende at opleve mange kunstig inducerede lucide drømme ofte nok.

source_text: The main reason for this phenomenon is the result of the lucid dreams expanding the length of time between REM states.
target_text: Hovedårsagen til dette fænomen er resultatet af de lyse drømme, der udvider længden af tiden mellem REM-tilstande.

source_text: With fewer REMs per night, this state in which you experience actual sleep and your body recovers becomes infrequent enough to become a problem.
target_text: Med færre REM'er om natten bliver denne tilstand, hvor du faktisk sover og din krop genvinder sig, så sjælden at det bliver et problem.

source_text: This is just as exhausting as if you were to wake up every twenty or thirty minutes and watch TV.
target_text: Det er lige så udmattende som at man vågner hver tyve eller tredive minut og ser fjernsyn.

source_text: The effect is dependent on how often your brain attempts to lucidly dream per night.
target_text: Effekten afhænger af hvor ofte din hjerne forsøger at drømme klart om natten.

source_text: Things did not go well for the Italians in North Africa almost from the start. Within a week of Italy's declaration of war on June 10, 1940, the British 11th Hussars had seized Fort Capuzzo in Libya.
target_text: Inden for en uge efter at Italien erklærede krig den 10. juni 1940 havde de britiske 11. hussare erobret Fort Capuzzo i Libyen.

source_text: In an ambush east of Bardia, the British captured the Italian Tenth Army's Engineer-in-Chief, General Lastucci.
target_text: I et baghold øst for Bardia fangede briterne den italienske tiende hærs øverstbefalende ingeniør, general Lastucci.

source_text: On June 28, Marshal Italo Balbo, the Governor-General of Libya and apparent heir to Mussolini, was killed by friendly fire while landing in Tobruk.
target_text: Den 28. juni blev marskal Italo Balbo, generalguvernøren for Libyen og Mussolinis tilsyneladende arvinger, dræbt af venligt skud, mens han landede i Tobruk.

source_text: The modern sport of fencing is played at many levels, from students learning at a university to professional and Olympic competition.
target_text: Den moderne sport spilles på mange niveauer, fra studerende der studerer på et universitet til professionelle og olympiske konkurrencer.

source_text: The sport is primarily played in a duel format, one fencer dueling another.
target_text: Spillet spilles primært i en duelleform, hvor en fencer duellerer med en anden.

source_text: Golf is a game in which players use clubs to hit balls into holes.
target_text: Golf er et spil hvor spillerne bruger klubber til at slå bolde i huller.

source_text: Eighteen holes are played during a regular round, with players usually starting on the first hole on the course and finishing on the eighteenth.
target_text: Der spilles 18 huller under en almindelig runde, hvor spillerne normalt starter på det første hul på banen og slutter på det 18..

source_text: The player who takes the fewest strokes, or swings of the club, to complete the course wins.
target_text: Den spiller der tager de færreste slag, eller svinger af klubben, for at fuldføre kurset, vinder.

source_text: The game is played on grass, and the grass around the hole is mown shorter and called the green.
target_text: Spillet spilles på græsset, og græsset omkring hullet bliver hugget kortere og kaldt grønt.

source_text: Perhaps the most common type of tourism is what most people associate with traveling: Recreation tourism.
target_text: Måske er den mest almindelige form for turisme, hvad de fleste mennesker forbinder med at rejse: rekreationsturisme.

source_text: This is when people go to a place that is very different from their regular day-to-day life to relax and have fun.
target_text: Det er når folk går til et sted der er meget anderledes end deres almindelige hverdag for at slappe af og have det sjovt.

source_text: Beaches, theme parks and camp grounds are often the most common places frequented by recreational tourists.
target_text: Stranden, temaparkken og campingpladserne er ofte de mest almindelige steder der besøges af rekreative turister.

source_text: If the objective of one’s visit to a particular place is to get to know its history and culture then this type of tourism is known as cultural tourism.
target_text: Hvis målet med et besøg på et bestemt sted er at lære dets historie og kultur at kende, kaldes denne type turisme kulturturisme.

source_text: Tourists may visit different landmarks of a particular country or they may simply opt to focus on just one area.
target_text: Turisterne kan besøge forskellige seværdigheder i et bestemt land, eller de kan blot vælge at fokusere på ét område.

source_text: The Colonists, seeing this activity, had also called for reinforcements.
target_text: Da kolonisterne så denne aktivitet, havde de også krævet forstærkninger.

source_text: Troops reinforcing the forward positions included the 1st and 3rd New Hampshire regiments of 200 men, under Colonels John Stark and James Reed (both later became generals).
target_text: Trupperne, der forstærkede de fremadgående positioner, omfattede 1. og 3. New Hampshire regiment med 200 mænd, under oberste John Stark og James Reed (både blev senere generaler).

source_text: Stark's men took positions along the fence on the north end of the Colonist's position.
target_text: Stark's mænd tog positioner langs hegnet på den nordlige ende af kolonistens position.

source_text: When low tide opened a gap along the Mystic River along the northeast of the peninsula, they quickly extended the fence with a short stone wall to the north ending at the water's edge on a small beach.
target_text: Da lavt tidevand åbnede et hul langs Mystic-floden langs den nordøstlige del af halvøen, udvidede de hurtigt hegnet med en kort stenmur nordpå og endte ved vandet på en lille strand.

source_text: Gridley or Stark placed a stake about 100 feet (30 m) in front of the fence and ordered that no one fire until the regulars passed it.
target_text: Gridley eller Stark placerede et pæl ca. 30 meter foran hegnet og beordrede at ingen skulle skyde før de almindelige passerede det.

source_text: The American plan relied on launching coordinated attacks from three different directions.
target_text: Den amerikanske plan var baseret på at lancere koordinerede angreb fra tre forskellige retninger.

source_text: General John Cadwalder would launch a diversionary attack against the British garrison at Bordentown, in order to block off any reinforcements.
target_text: General John Cadwalder ville lancere et distraktionsangreb mod den britiske garnison i Bordentown for at blokere for enhver forstærkning.

source_text: General James Ewing would take 700 militia across the river at Trenton Ferry, seize the bridge over the Assunpink Creek and prevent any enemy troops from escaping.
target_text: General James Ewing ville tage 700 militser over floden ved Trenton Ferry, tage broen over Assunpink Creek og forhindre fjendens tropper i at flygte.

source_text: The main assault force of 2,400 men would cross the river nine miles north of Trenton, and then split into two groups, one under Greene and one under Sullivan, in order to launch a pre-dawn attack.
target_text: Den vigtigste angrebsstyrke på 2.400 mænd skulle krydse floden ni miles nord for Trenton, og derefter opdele sig i to grupper, en under Greene og en under Sullivan, for at lancere et angreb før daggry.

source_text: With the change from the quarter to the half mile run, speed becomes of much less importance and endurance becomes an absolute necessity.
target_text: Når man skifter fra et kvarter til et halvt mil, bliver hastigheden mindre vigtig og udholdenheden bliver en absolut nødvendighed.

source_text: Of course a first-class half-miler, a man who can beat two minutes, must be possessed of a fair amount of speed, but endurance must be cultivated at all hazards.
target_text: Selvfølgelig skal en førsteklasses halvmiler, en mand, der kan slå to minutter, have en rimelig hastighed, men udholdenhed skal dyrkes under alle farer.

source_text: Some cross country running during the winter, combined with gymnasium work for the upper part of the body, is the best preparation for the running season.
target_text: At løbe på tværs af landet om vinteren, kombineret med at arbejde i gymnasiet for den øverste del af kroppen, er den bedste forberedelse til løbesæsonen.

source_text: Proper nutritional practices alone cannot generate elite performances, but they can significantly affect young athletes' overall wellness.
target_text: Gode ernæringsmetoder alene kan ikke skabe eliteoptrædener, men de kan betydeligt påvirke unge idrætters generelle velvære.

source_text: Maintaining a healthy energy balance, practicing effective hydration habits, and understanding the various aspects of supplementation practices can help athletes improve their performance and increase their enjoyment of the sport.
target_text: At opretholde en sund energibalance, praktisere effektive hydrationsvaner og forstå de forskellige aspekter af kosttilskud kan hjælpe idrætsudøvere med at forbedre deres præstationer og øge deres nydelse af sporten.

source_text: Middle distance running is a relatively inexpensive sport; however, there are many misconceptions regarding the few pieces of equipment required to participate.
target_text: Løb på mellemlang afstand er en relativt billig sport; der er dog mange misforståelser om de få dele af udstyr, der kræves for at deltage.

source_text: Products can be purchased as needed, but most will have little or no real impact on performance.
target_text: Produkterne kan købes efter behov, men de fleste vil få ringe eller ingen reel effekt på ydeevnen.

source_text: Athletes may feel that they prefer a product even when it provides no real benefits.
target_text: Idrettsfolk føler måske at de foretrækker et produkt, selv når det ikke giver nogen reelle fordele.

source_text: The atom can be considered to be one of the fundamental building blocks of all matter.
target_text: Atomet kan betragtes som en af de grundlæggende byggesten i al materie.

source_text: Its a very complex entity which consists, according to a simplified Bohr model, of a central nucleus orbited by electrons, somewhat similar to planets orbiting the sun - see Figure 1.1.
target_text: Det er en meget kompleks enhed, der ifølge en forenklet Bohr-model består af en central kerne omgivet af elektroner, som ligner planeter omgivet af solen - se figur 1.1.

source_text: The nucleus consists of two particles - neutrons and protons.
target_text: Kernen består af to partikler - neutroner og protoner.

source_text: Protons have a positive electric charge while neutrons have no charge. The electrons have a negative electric charge.
target_text: Protoner har en positiv elektrisk ladning, mens neutroner har ingen ladning.

source_text: To Check the victim, you must first survey the scene to ensure your safety.
target_text: For at kontrollere offeret, skal du først undersøge stedet for at sikre din sikkerhed.

source_text: You need to notice the victim's position as you approach him or her and any automatic red flags.
target_text: Du skal bemærke offerets position, når du nærmer dig ham eller hende og eventuelle automatiske røde flag.

source_text: If you get hurt trying to help, you may only serve to make matters worse.
target_text: Hvis du bliver såret ved at hjælpe, kan du kun gøre det værre.

source_text: The study found that depression, fear and catastrophising mediated the relationship between pain and disability in lower back pain sufferers.
target_text: Undersøgelsen viste, at depression, frygt og katastrofering medierede forholdet mellem smerte og handicap hos personer med nederste rygsmerter.

source_text: Only the effects of catastrophizing, not depression and fear was conditional of regular weekly structured PA sessions.
target_text: Kun virkningerne af katastrofer, ikke depression og frygt var betinget af regelmæssig ugentligt struktureret PA-sessioner.

source_text: Those participating in regular activity required more support in terms of negative perception of pain distinguishing the differences of chronic pain and discomfort feel from normal physical movement.
target_text: De, der deltog i regelmæssig aktivitet, havde brug for mere støtte med hensyn til en negativ opfattelse af smerten, idet der var forskel på, hvordan kronisk smerte og ubehag føltes i forhold til normal fysisk bevægelse.

source_text: Vision, or the ability to see depends on visual system sensory organs or eyes.
target_text: Synet eller evnen til at se afhænger af synsorganer eller øjnene.

source_text: There are many different constructions of eyes, ranging in complexity depending on the requirements of the organism.
target_text: Der er mange forskellige øjenkonstruktioner, som varierer i kompleksitet afhængigt af organismens krav.

source_text: The different constructions have different capabilities, are sensitive to different wave-lengths and have differing degrees of acuity, also they require different processing to make sense of the input and different numbers to work optimally.
target_text: De forskellige konstruktioner har forskellige evner, er følsomme over for forskellige bølgelængder og har forskellige grader af skarphed, og de kræver også forskellig behandling for at forstå indgangen og de forskellige tal for at fungere optimalt.

source_text: A population is the collection of organisms of a particular species within a given geographic area.
target_text: En population er en samling af organismer af en bestemt art inden for et givet geografisk område.

source_text: When all individuals in a population are identical with regard to a particular phenotypic trait they are known as monomorphic.
target_text: Når alle individer i en befolkning er identiske med hensyn til et bestemt fenotypisk træk, kaldes de monomorf.

source_text: When the individuals show several variants of a particular trait they are polymorphic.
target_text: Når individerne viser flere varianter af et bestemt træk, er de polymorfe.

source_text: Army ant colonies march and nest in different phases as well.
target_text: Militærmørekolonier marcherer og nestes også i forskellige faser.

source_text: In the nomadic phase, army ants march at night and stop to camp during the day.
target_text: I den nomadiske fase marcherer hærmyre om natten og stopper til lejren om dagen.

source_text: The colony begins a nomadic phase when available food has decreased. During this phase, the colony makes temporary nests that are changed everyday.
target_text: Kolonien begynder en nomadisk fase, når den tilgængelige mad er reduceret.

source_text: Each of these nomadic rampages or marches lasts for approximately 17 days.
target_text: Hver af disse nomadiske kampagner eller marcher varer i ca. 17 dage.

source_text: What is a cell? The word cell comes from the Latin word "cella", meaning "small room", and it was first coined by a microscopist observing the structure of cork.
target_text: Hvad er en celle? Ordet celle kommer fra det latinske ord "cella", som betyder "små rum", og det blev først opfundet af en mikroskopist som observerede korksstrukturen.

source_text: The cell is the basic unit of all living things, and all organisms are composed of one or more cells.
target_text: Cellen er den grundlæggende enhed i alle levende væsener, og alle organismer består af en eller flere celler.

source_text: Cells are so basic and critical to the study of life, in fact, that they are often referred to as "the building blocks of life".
target_text: Celler er så grundlæggende og afgørende for at studere liv, at de ofte kaldes "livets byggesten".

source_text: The Nervous System maintains homeostasis by sending nerve impulses through out the body to keep the flow of blood going as well as undisturbed.
target_text: Nervesystemet opretholder homeostasen ved at sende nerveimpulser ud i kroppen for at holde blodgennemstrømningen i gang og uden forstyrrelser.

source_text: These nerve impulses can be sent so quickly throughout the body which helps keep the body safe from any potential threat.
target_text: Disse nerveimpulser kan sendes så hurtigt over hele kroppen, som hjælper med at holde kroppen sikker fra enhver potentiel trussel.

source_text: Tornadoes strike a small area compared to other violent storms, but they can destroy everything in their path.
target_text: Tornadoer rammer et lille område sammenlignet med andre voldsomme storme, men de kan ødelægge alt på deres vej.

source_text: Tornadoes uproot trees, rip boards from buildings, and fling cars up into the sky. The most violent two percent of tornadoes last more than three hours.
target_text: De mest voldsomme to procent af tornadoerne varer mere end tre timer.

source_text: These monster storms have winds up to 480 km/h (133 m/s; 300 mph).
target_text: Disse monster storme har vinder op til 480 km/t (133 m/s; 300 mph).

source_text: Humans have been making and using lenses for magnification for thousands and thousands of years.
target_text: Mennesker har lavet og brugt linser til forstørrelse i tusindvis af år.

source_text: However, the first true telescopes were made in Europe in the late 16th century.
target_text: Men de første sande teleskoper blev lavet i Europa i slutningen af det 16. århundrede.

source_text: These telescopes used a combination of two lenses to make distant objects appear both nearer and larger.
target_text: Disse teleskoper brugte en kombination af to linser for at få fjerntliggende objekter til at se både tættere og større ud.

source_text: Greed and selfishness will always be with us and it is the nature of cooperation that when the majority benefit there will always be more to gain in the short term by acting selfishly
target_text: Vi vil altid have grådighed og egoisme med os, og det er samarbejdets natur, at når flertallet får gavn, vil der altid være mere at vinde på kort sigt ved at handle egoistisk.

source_text: Hopefully, most people will realise that their long term best option is to work together with others.
target_text: Forhåbentlig vil de fleste mennesker indse at deres bedste løsning på lang sigt er at samarbejde med andre.

source_text: Many people dream of the day when humans can travel to another star and explore other worlds, some people wonder what's out there some belive that aliens or other life may live on another plant.
target_text: Mange mennesker drømmer om den dag, hvor mennesker kan rejse til en anden stjerne og udforske andre verdener, nogle mennesker undrer sig over, hvad der er derude nogle tror, at rumvæsener eller andet liv kan leve på en anden plante.

source_text: But, if this ever does happen probably won't happen for a very long time. The stars are so spread out that there are trillions of miles between stars that are "neighbors".
target_text: Men hvis dette nogensinde sker, vil det sandsynligvis ikke ske for meget lang tid. Stjernerne er så spredt ud at der er milliarder af kilometer mellem stjerner der er "naboer".

source_text: Maybe one day, your great grandchildren will be standing atop an alien world wondering about their ancient ancestors?
target_text: Måske en dag vil dine storebarn stå på toppen af en fremmed verden og spekulere på deres forfædre?

source_text: Animals are made of many cells. They eat things and digest them inside. Most animals can move.
target_text: Dyr er lavet af mange celler. De spiser ting og fordøjer dem inde i dem. De fleste dyr kan bevæge sig.

source_text: Only animals have brains (though not even all animals do; jellyfish, for example, do not have brains).
target_text: Kun dyr har hjerne (selv om ikke alle dyr gør det; f.eks. meduser har ingen hjerne).

source_text: Animals are found all over the earth. They dig in the ground, swim in the oceans, and fly in the sky.
target_text: Dyr findes overalt på jorden. De graver i jorden, svømmer i havet og flyver i himlen.

source_text: A cell is the smallest structural and functional unit of a living (things) organism.
target_text: En celle er den mindste strukturelle og funktionelle enhed i en levende organisme.

source_text: Cell comes from the Latin word cella which means small room.
target_text: Cell kommer fra det latinske ord cella, som betyder lille rum.

source_text: If you look at living things under a microscope, you will see that they are made of small squares or balls.
target_text: Hvis man kigger på levende organismer under et mikroskop, kan man se at de er lavet af små kvadrater eller kugler.

source_text: Robert Hooke, a biologist from England, saw small squares in cork with a microscope.
target_text: Robert Hooke, en biolog fra England, så små kvadrater i kork med et mikroskop.

source_text: They looked like rooms. He was the first person to observe dead cells
target_text: Han var den første til at observere døde celler.

source_text: Elements and compounds can move from one state to another and not change.
