target_text: Elementer og forbindelser kan bevæge sig fra en tilstand til en anden og ikke ændre sig.

source_text: Nitrogen as a gas still has the same properties as liquid nitrogen. The liquid state is denser but the molecules are still the same.
target_text: Nitrogen som en gas har stadig de samme egenskaber som flydende nitrogen. Den flydende tilstand er tættere, men molekylerne er stadig de samme.

source_text: Water is another example. The compound water is made up of two hydrogen atoms and one oxygen atom.
target_text: Vand er et andet eksempel: Det sammensatte vand består af to hydrogenatomer og et iltatom.

source_text: It has the same molecular structure whether it is a gas, liquid, or solid.
target_text: Den har den samme molekylære struktur, uanset om den er en gas, væske eller fast.

source_text: Although its physical state may change, its chemical state remains the same.
target_text: Selv om dens fysiske tilstand kan ændre sig, forbliver dens kemiske tilstand den samme.

source_text: Time is something that is all around us, and affects everything we do, yet is difficult to understand.
target_text: Tiden er noget, der er overalt omkring os, og påvirker alt, hvad vi gør, men det er svært at forstå.

source_text: Time has been studied by religious, philosophical, and scientific scholars for thousands of years.
target_text: Tiden er blevet studeret af religiøse, filosofiske og videnskabelige forskere i tusindvis af år.

source_text: We experience time as a series of events passing from the future through the present to the past.
target_text: Vi oplever tid som en række begivenheder, der går fra fremtiden gennem nutiden til fortiden.

source_text: Time is also how we compare the duration (length) of events.
target_text: Tiden er også hvordan vi sammenligner begivenhedernes varighed (længde).

source_text: You can mark the passing of time yourself by observing the repetition of a cyclical event. A cyclical event is something that happens again and again regularly.
target_text: Man kan selv markere tidens gang ved at observere gentagelsen af en cyklisk begivenhed.

source_text: Computers today are used to manipulate pictures and videos.
target_text: I dag bruges computere til at manipulere billeder og videoer.

source_text: Sophisticated animations can be constructed on computers, and this kind of animation is increasingly being used in television and films.
target_text: Raffinerede animationer kan bygges på computere, og denne form for animation bruges i stigende grad i fjernsyn og film.

source_text: Music is often recorded using sophisticated computers to process and mix sounds together.
target_text: Musik optages ofte ved hjælp af avancerede computere for at behandle og blande lyd sammen.

source_text: For a long time during the nineteenth and twentieth centuries, it was believed the first inhabitants of New Zealand were the Maori people, who hunted giant birds called moas.
target_text: I det 19. og 20. århundrede blev det længe antaget, at de første indbyggere i New Zealand var maorerne, der jagtede gigantiske fugle kaldet moas.

source_text: The theory then established the idea that the Maori people migrated from Polynesia in a Great Fleet and took New Zealand from the Moriori, establishing an agricultural society.
target_text: Teorien etablerede derefter ideen om, at Maori-folket migrerede fra Polynesien i en stor flåde og tog New Zealand fra Moriori-folket og etablerede et landbrugssamfund.

source_text: However, new evidence suggests that the Moriori were a group of mainland Maori who migrated from New Zealand to the Chatham Islands, developing their own distinctive, peaceful culture.
target_text: Men nye beviser tyder på, at Moriori-folket var en gruppe af fastlandet Maori, der flyttede fra New Zealand til Chathamøerne og udviklede deres egen særprægede, fredelige kultur.

source_text: There was also another tribe on the Chatham islands these were Maori who migrated away from New Zealand.
target_text: Der var også en anden stamme på Chatham øerne disse var Maori, der migrerede væk fra New Zealand.

source_text: They called themselves the Moriori there were a few skirmishes and in the end, the Moriori were wiped out
target_text: De kaldte sig selv Moriori. Der var nogle skænderier, og til sidst blev Moriorierne udryddet.

source_text: Individuals who had been involved for several decades helped us appreciate our strengths and passions while candidly assessing difficulties and even failures.
target_text: Personer der havde været involveret i flere årtier, hjalp os til at sætte pris på vores styrker og lidenskaber og samtidig ærligt vurdere vanskeligheder og endda fejl.

source_text: While listening to individuals share their individual, family, and organizational stories, we gained valuable insight into the past and some of the personalities who influenced for good or ill the culture of the organization.
target_text: Mens vi lyttede til hvor enkeltpersoner fortalte deres personlige, familie- og organisationshistorier, fik vi værdifuld indsigt i fortiden og i nogle af de personer der for godt eller ondt påvirkede organisationens kultur.

source_text: While understanding one’s history does not assume understanding of culture, it does at least help people gain a sense of where they fall within the history of the organization.
target_text: Selv om forståelsen af en persons historie ikke forudsætter en forståelse af kulturen, hjælper den i det mindste folk med at få en fornemmelse af, hvor de hører ind i organisationens historie.

source_text: While assessing the successes and becoming aware of failures, individuals and the whole of the participating persons discover more deeply the values, mission, and driving forces of the organization.
target_text: Mens de vurderer succeserne og bliver opmærksomme på fiaskoer, opdager enkeltpersoner og de deltagende i sin helhed mere dybt organisationens værdier, mission og drivkræfter.

source_text: In this instance, recalling previous instances of entrepreneurial behavior and resulting successes helped people to be open to new changes and new direction for the local church.
target_text: I dette tilfælde hjalp det folk at være åbne for nye forandringer og nye retninger for den lokale kirke ved at huske tidligere eksempler på iværksætteradfærd og de resultater, der blev opnået.

source_text: Such success stories lessened the fears of change, while creating positive inclinations toward change in the future.
target_text: Sådanne succeshistorier mindskede frygt for forandring og skabte samtidig positive tilbøjeligheder til forandring i fremtiden.

source_text: Convergent thinking patterns are problem solving techniques that unite different ideas or fields to find a solution.
target_text: Konvergent tænkning er problemløsningsteknikker, der forener forskellige ideer eller områder for at finde en løsning.

source_text: The focus of this mindset is speed, logic and accuracy, also identification of facts, reapplying existing techniques, gathering information.
target_text: Fokus på denne tankegang er hastighed, logik og nøjagtighed, også identifikation af fakta, genanvendelse af eksisterende teknikker, indsamling af oplysninger.

source_text: The most important factor of this mindset is: there is only one correct answer. You only think of two answers, namely right or wrong.
target_text: Den vigtigste faktor i denne tankegang er, at der kun er ét rigtigt svar. Man tænker kun på to svar, nemlig rigtigt eller forkert.

source_text: This type of thinking is associated with certain science or standard procedures.
target_text: Denne form for tænkning er forbundet med visse videnskaber eller standardprocedurer.

source_text: People with this type of thinking have logical thinking, are able to memorize patterns, solve problems and work on scientific tests.
target_text: Mennesker med denne type tænkning har logisk tænkning, er i stand til at huske mønstre, løse problemer og arbejde på videnskabelige tests.

source_text: Humans are by far the most talented species in reading the minds of others.
target_text: Mennesker er langt den mest talentfulde art i at læse andres tanker.

source_text: That means we are able to successfully predict what other humans perceive, intend, believe, know or desire.
target_text: Det betyder at vi er i stand til med succes at forudsige, hvad andre mennesker opfatter, har til hensigt, tror, ved eller ønsker.

source_text: Among these abilities, understanding the intention of others is crucial. It allows us to resolve possible ambiguities of physical actions.
target_text: Blandt disse evner er det afgørende at forstå andres hensigter. Det giver os mulighed for at løse eventuelle tvetydighed i fysiske handlinger.

source_text: For example, if you were to see someone breaking a car window, you would probably assume he was trying to steal a stranger’s car.
target_text: Hvis man f.eks. skulle se nogen bryde et vindue i en bil, ville man antage at han prøvede at stjæle en fremmeds bil.

source_text: He would need to be judged differently if he had lost his car keys and it was his own car that he was trying to break into.
target_text: Han skulle dømmes anderledes, hvis han havde mistet bilnøglerne, og det var hans egen bil, han forsøgte at bryde ind i.

source_text: MRI is based on a physics phenomenon called nuclear magnetic resonance (NMR), which was discovered in the 1930s by Felix Bloch (working at Stanford University) and Edward Purcell (from Harvard University).
target_text: MRI er baseret på et fysikfenomen kaldet atommagnetisk resonans (NMR), som blev opdaget i 1930'erne af Felix Bloch (arbejdende ved Stanford University) og Edward Purcell (fra Harvard University).

source_text: In this resonance, magnetic field and radio waves cause atoms to give off tiny radio signals.
target_text: I denne resonans får magnetfelt og radiobølger atomer til at udsende små radiosignaler.

source_text: In the year 1970, Raymond Damadian, a medical doctor and research scientist, discovered the basis for using magnetic resonance imaging as a tool for medical diagnosis.
target_text: I 1970 opdagede Raymond Damadian, en læge og forsker, grundlaget for at bruge magnetresonansbilleddannelse som et værktøj til medicinsk diagnose.

source_text: Four years later a patent was granted, which was the world's first patent issued in the field of MRI.
target_text: Fire år senere blev patent udstedt, hvilket var verdens første patent på området MRI.

source_text: In 1977, Dr. Damadian completed the construction of the first “whole-body” MRI scanner, which he called the ”Indomitable”.
target_text: I 1977 fuldførte Dr. Damadian konstruktionen af den første  hele kroppen  MRI-scanner, som han kaldte Indomitable.

source_text: Asynchronous communication encourages time for reflection and reaction to others.
target_text: Asynkron kommunikation giver tid til at reflektere og reagere på andre.

source_text: It allows students the ability to work at their own pace and control the pace of instructional information.
target_text: Det giver eleverne mulighed for at arbejde i deres eget tempo og kontrollere undervisningstidens tempo.

source_text: In addition, there are fewer time restrictions with the possibility of flexible working hours. (Bremer, 1998)
target_text: Desuden er der færre tidsbegrænsninger med mulighed for fleksibelt arbejdstid (Bremer, 1998).

source_text: The use of the Internet and the World Wide Web allows learners to have access to information at all times.
target_text: Anvendelsen af internettet og World Wide Web giver eleverne adgang til oplysninger til enhver tid.

source_text: Students can also submit questions to instructors at any time of day and expect reasonably quick responses, rather than waiting until the next face-to-face meeting.
target_text: Studerende kan også stille instruktorerne spørgsmål til enhver tid på dagen og forvente rimeligt hurtige svar i stedet for at vente til det næste møde ansigt til ansigt.

source_text: The postmodern approach to learning offers the freedom from absolutes. There is no one good way to learn.
target_text: Den postmoderne tilgang til læring giver frihed fra absoluter.

source_text: In fact, there is not one good thing to learn.Learning takes place in the experience between the learner and the knowledge presented.
target_text: Der er faktisk ikke noget godt at lære.Læring finder sted i oplevelsen mellem den studerende og den viden, der præsenteres.

source_text: Our current experience with all the do-it-yourself and information presenting, learning-based television shows illustrates this point.
target_text: Vores nuværende erfaring med alle de gør-det-selv- og informationspræsenterende, læringsbaserede tv-programmer illustrerer dette punkt.

source_text: So many of us find ourselves watching a television show that informs us of a process or experience in which we will never participate or apply that knowledge.
target_text: Så mange af os ser et tv-program, der fortæller os om en proces eller en oplevelse, hvor vi aldrig vil deltage eller anvende den viden.

source_text: We will never overhaul a car, build a fountain in our backyard, travel to Peru to examine ancient ruins, or remodel our neighbour's house.
target_text: Vi vil aldrig renovere en bil, bygge en kilde i vores baghave, rejse til Peru for at undersøge gamle ruiner eller ombygge naboens hus.

source_text: Thanks to undersea fiber optic cable links to Europe and broadband satellite, Greenland is well connected with 93% of the population having internet access.
target_text: Grønland er godt forbundet med underjordiske fiberoptickabelforbindelser til Europa og bredbåndssatellit, og 93% af befolkningen har adgang til internettet.

source_text: Your hotel or hosts (if staying in a guesthouse or private home) will likely have wifi or an internet connected PC, and all settlements have an internet cafe or some location with public wifi.
target_text: Dine hoteller eller værter (hvis du bor i et gæstehus eller et privat hjem) vil sandsynligvis have wifi eller en internetforbundet pc, og alle bosættelser har en internetkafé eller et sted med offentlig wifi.

source_text: As mentioned above, though the word "Eskimo" remains acceptable in the United States, it is considered pejorative by many non-U.S. Arctic peoples, especially in Canada.
target_text: Som nævnt ovenfor, er ordet "Eskimo" stadig acceptabelt i USA, men det betragtes som nedværdigende af mange ikke-amerikanske arktiske folk, især i Canada.

source_text: While you may hear the word used by Greenlandic Natives, its use should be avoided by foreigners.
target_text: Selv om du måske hører ordet brugt af grønlandske indfødte, bør udlændinge undgå at bruge det.

source_text: The native inhabitants of Greenland call themselves Inuit in Canada and Kalaalleq (plural Kalaallit), a Greenlander, in Greenland.
target_text: De indfødte indbyggere i Grønland kalder sig inuit i Canada og Kalaalleq (flertal Kalaallit), en grønlander, i Grønland.

source_text: Crime, and ill-will toward foreigners in general, is virtually unknown in Greenland. Even in the towns, there are no "rough areas."
target_text: Kriminalitet og ond vilje over for udlændinge i almindelighed er stort set ukendt i Grønland.

source_text: Cold weather is perhaps the only real danger the unprepared will face.
target_text: Koldt vejr er måske den eneste virkelige fare de uforberedte vil stå over for.

source_text: If you visit Greenland during cold seasons (considering that the further north you go, the colder it will be), it is essential to bring warm enough clothing.
target_text: Hvis du besøger Grønland i koldesæsonen (hvis du går længere nordpå, så er det koldere), er det vigtigt at tage nok varmt tøj med.

source_text: The very long days in the summer can lead to problems getting sufficient sleep and associated health issues.
target_text: De meget lange dage om sommeren kan føre til problemer med at få nok søvn og dermed forbundet sundhedsproblemer.

source_text: During the summer, also watch out for the Nordic mosquitoes. Although they do not transmit any diseases, they can be irritating.
target_text: I løbet af sommeren skal man også passe på de nordiske myg, der ikke overfører nogen sygdomme, men kan være irriterende.

source_text: While San Francisco's economy is linked to it being a world-class tourist attraction, its economy is diversified.
target_text: San Franciscos økonomi er forbundet med at være en turistattraktion i verdensklasse, men dens økonomi er diversificeret.

source_text: The largest employment sectors are professional services, government, finance, trade, and tourism.
target_text: De største beskæftigelsessektorer er faglige tjenester, regering, finans, handel og turisme.

source_text: Its frequent portrayal in music, films, literature and popular culture has helped make the city and its landmarks known throughout the world.
target_text: Dens hyppige portrættering i musik, film, litteratur og populærkultur har bidraget til at gøre byen og dens seværdigheder kendt over hele verden.

source_text: San Francisco has developed a large tourist infrastructure with numerous hotels, restaurants, and top-notch convention facilities.
target_text: San Francisco har udviklet en stor turistinfrastruktur med mange hoteller, restauranter og top-notch kongresfaciliteter.

source_text: San Francisco is also one of the best places in the nation for other Asian cuisine: Korean, Thai, Indian, and Japanese.
target_text: San Francisco er også et af de bedste steder i landet for andre asiatiske retter: koreansk, thailandsk, indisk og japansk.

source_text: Traveling to Walt Disney World represents a major pilgrimage for many American families.
target_text: At rejse til Walt Disney World er en stor pilgrimsrejse for mange amerikanske familier.

source_text: The "typical" visit involves flying into Orlando International Airport, busing to an on-site Disney hotel, spending about a week without leaving Disney property, and returning home.
target_text: Det "typiske" besøg indebærer at flyve ind på Orlando International Airport, tage bus til et Disney-hotel på stedet, tilbringe omkring en uge uden at forlade Disney-ejendommen og vende hjem.

source_text: There are infinite variations possible, but this remains what most people mean when they talk of "going to Disney World".
target_text: Der er uendelige variationer, men det er stadig hvad de fleste mener, når de taler om at gå til Disney World.

source_text: Many tickets sold online through auction websites such as eBay or Craigslist are partially used multi-day park-hopper tickets.
target_text: Mange billetter, der sælges online via auktionswebsteder som eBay eller Craigslist, bruges delvis til flere dages parkhopperbilletter.

source_text: While this is a very common activity, it is prohibited by Disney: the tickets are non-transferable.
target_text: Selv om dette er en meget almindelig aktivitet, er det forbudt af Disney: billetterne er ikke overførbare.

source_text: Any camping below the rim in Grand Canyon requires a backcountry permit.
target_text: Enhver camping under kanten i Grand Canyon kræver en backcountry tilladelse.

source_text: Permits are limited to protect the canyon, and become available on the 1st day of the month, four months prior to the start month.
target_text: Tilladelser er begrænset til at beskytte kanjonen, og bliver tilgængelige den første dag i måneden, fire måneder før startmåneden.

source_text: Thus, a backcountry permit for any start date in May becomes available on 1 Jan.
target_text: Således bliver en backcountry-tilladelse til enhver startdato i maj tilgængelig den 1. januar.

source_text: Space for the most popular areas, such as the Bright Angel Campground adjacent to Phantom Ranch, generally fill up by the requests received on first date they are opened to reservations.
target_text: Rum til de mest populære områder, såsom Bright Angel Campground ved siden af Phantom Ranch, er generelt fyldt med anmodninger modtaget på den første dato de er åbne for reservationer.

source_text: There are a limited number permits reserved for walk-in requests available on a first come, first served basis.
target_text: Der er et begrænset antal tilladelser, der er reserveret til indkøbsanmodninger.

source_text: Entering Southern Africa by car is an amazing way to see all the region's beauty as well as to get to places off the normal tourist routes.
target_text: At komme ind i det sydlige Afrika med bil er en fantastisk måde at se al regionens skønhed på samt at komme til steder uden for de normale turistruter.

source_text: This can be done in a normal car with careful planning but a 4x4 is highly advised and many locations are only accessible with a high wheel base 4x4.
target_text: Dette kan gøres i en normal bil med omhyggelig planlægning, men en 4x4 anbefales meget, og mange steder er kun tilgængelige med en høj hjulbase 4x4.

source_text: Keep in mind while planning that although Southern Africa is stable not all neighboring countries are.
target_text: Husk under planlægningen at selv om det sydlige Afrika er stabilt, er det ikke alle nabolande.

source_text: Visa requirements and costs vary from nation to nation and are affected by the country you come from.
target_text: Visumkrav og omkostninger varierer fra land til land og afhænger af det land, du kommer fra.

source_text: Each country also has unique laws requiring what emergency items need to be in the car.
target_text: Hvert land har også unikke love om, hvilke nødartikler der skal være i bilen.

source_text: Victoria Falls is a town in the western portion of Zimbabwe, across the border from Livingstone, Zambia, and near Botswana.
target_text: Victoria Falls er en by i den vestlige del af Zimbabwe, over grænsen til Livingstone, Zambia, og nær Botswana.

source_text: The town lies immediately next to the falls, and they are the major attraction, but this popular tourist destination offers both adventure seekers and sightseers plenty of opportunities for a longer stay.
target_text: Byen ligger lige ved siden af vandfaldene, og de er den største attraktion, men dette populære turistmål tilbyder både eventyrlystne og sightseers masser af muligheder for et længere ophold.

source_text: In the rainy season (November to March), the water volume will be higher and the Falls will be more dramatic.
target_text: I regnsæsonen (november til marts) vil vandmængden være højere, og vandfaldene vil være mere dramatiske.

source_text: You are guaranteed to get wet if you cross the bridge or walk along the trails winding near the Falls.
target_text: Du er garanteret våd hvis du krydser broen eller går langs de svingende stier i nærheden af Falls.

source_text: On the other hand, it is precisely because the volume of water is so high that your viewing of the actual Falls will be obscured—by all the water!
target_text: På den anden side er det netop fordi vandmængden er så høj, at dit syn på de faktiske Falls vil blive dækket af alt vandet!

source_text: Tomb of Tutankhamun (KV62). KV62 may be the most famous of the tombs in the Valley, the scene of Howard Carter's 1922 discovery of the almost intact royal burial of the young king.
target_text: Tutankhamons grav (KV62). KV62 kan være den mest berømte af gravene i dalen, scenen for Howard Carters opdagelse i 1922 af den næsten intakte kongelige begravelse af den unge konge.

source_text: Compared to most of the other royal tombs, however, the tomb of Tutankhamun is barely worth visiting, being much smaller and with limited decoration.
target_text: Sammenlignet med de fleste andre kongelige graver er Tutankhamons grav dog knapt værd at besøge, fordi den er meget mindre og kun har begrænset dekoration.

source_text: Anyone interested in seeing evidence of the damage to the mummy done during attempts to remove it from the coffin will be disappointed as only the head and shoulders are visible.
target_text: Enhver der er interesseret i at se beviser for de skader på mumien, der er sket under forsøg på at fjerne den fra kisten, vil blive skuffet, da kun hovedet og skuldrene er synlige.

source_text: The fabulous riches of the tomb are no longer in it, but have been removed to the Egyptian Museum in Cairo.
target_text: Gravens fantastiske rigdomme er ikke længere i den, men er blevet overført til det egyptiske museum i Kairo.

source_text: Visitors with limited time would be best to spend their time elsewhere.
target_text: Besøgende med begrænset tid ville være bedst at tilbringe deres tid et andet sted.

source_text: Phnom Krom, 12 km southwest of Siem Reap. This hilltop temple was built at the end of the 9th century, during the reign of King Yasovarman.
target_text: Phnom Krom, 12 km sydvest for Siem Reap.

source_text: The gloomy atmosphere of the temple and the view over the Tonle Sap lake make the climb to the hill worthwhile.
target_text: Den mørke atmosfære i templet og udsigten over Tonle Sap-sjøen gør opstigningen til bjerget værd.

source_text: A visit to the site can be conveniently combined with a boat trip to the lake.
target_text: Et besøg på stedet kan hensigtsmæssigt kombineres med en bådrejse til søen.

source_text: The Angkor Pass is needed to enter the temple so do not forget to bring your passport along when heading to Tonle Sap.
target_text: Angkorpassen er nødvendig for at komme ind i templet, så glem ikke at tage dit pas med, når du tager til Tonle Sap.

source_text: Jerusalem is the capital and largest city of Israel, though most other countries and the United Nations do not recognize it as Israel's capital.
target_text: Jerusalem er Israels hovedstad og største by, selv om de fleste andre lande og FN ikke anerkender det som Israels hovedstad.

source_text: The ancient city in the Judean Hills has a fascinating history spanning thousands of years.
target_text: Den gamle by i Judæas bjerge har en fascinerende historie der strækker sig over tusindvis af år.

source_text: The city is holy to the three monotheistic religions - Judaism, Christianity and Islam, and serves as a spiritual, religious, and cultural center.
target_text: Byen er hellig for de tre monoteistiske religioner - jødedommen, kristendommen og islam - og fungerer som et åndeligt, religiøst og kulturelt centrum.

source_text: Due to the religious significance of the city, and in particular the many sites of the Old City area, Jerusalem is one of the main tourist destinations in Israel.
target_text: På grund af byens religiøse betydning, og især de mange steder i det gamle byområde, er Jerusalem et af de vigtigste turistmål i Israel.

source_text: Jerusalem has many historic, archeological and cultural sites, along with vibrant and crowded shopping centers, cafés, and restaurants.
target_text: Jerusalem har mange historiske, arkæologiske og kulturelle steder samt pulserende og overfyldte indkøbscentre, caféer og restauranter.

source_text: Ecuador requires that Cuban citizens receive an invitation letter prior to entering Ecuador through international airports or frontier admission points.
target_text: Ecuador kræver, at cubanske statsborgere modtager et invitationsbrev, før de kommer ind i Ecuador via internationale lufthavne eller grænseindgangssteder.

source_text: This letter must be legalized by the Ecuadorian Ministry of Foreign Affairs, and comply with certain requirements.
target_text: Dette brev skal være legaliseret af Ecuadors udenrigsministerium og være i overensstemmelse med visse krav.

source_text: These requirements are designed to provide an organized migratory flow between both countries.
target_text: Disse krav er designet til at sikre en organiseret migrationsstrøm mellem de to lande.

source_text: Cuban citizens who are US green card holders should visit an Ecuadorian Consulate to obtain an exemption to this requirement.
target_text: De cubanske statsborgere, der er indehavere af et amerikansk green card, bør besøge et ekvadorisk konsulat for at opnå fritagelse for dette krav.

source_text: Your passport must be valid for at least 6 months beyond your travel dates. A round/onward trip ticket is needed to prove the length of your stay.
target_text: Passet skal være gyldigt i mindst 6 måneder efter rejsedatoen.

source_text: Tours are cheaper for larger groups, so if you're by yourself or with just one friend, try to meet other people and form a group of four to six for a better per-person rate.
target_text: Turer er billigere for større grupper, så hvis du er alene eller kun med en ven, prøv at møde andre mennesker og danne en gruppe på fire til seks for en bedre pr. person pris.

source_text: However, this shouldn't really be off your concern, because often tourists are shuffled around to fill the cars.
target_text: Men det burde ikke være af din interesse, for ofte bliver turister blandet rundt for at fylde bilerne.

source_text: It seems actually to be more a way of tricking people into believing they have to pay more.
target_text: Det virker faktisk mere som en måde at narre folk til at tro, at de skal betale mere.

source_text: Towering above the north end of Machu Picchu is this steep mountain, often the backdrop to many photos of the ruins.
target_text: Over den nordlige ende af Machu Picchu ligger dette stejle bjerg, som ofte er baggrunden for mange billeder af ruinerne.

source_text: It looks a bit daunting from below, and it is a steep and difficult ascent, but most reasonably fit persons should be able to make it in about 45 minutes.
target_text: Det ser lidt skræmmende ud fra nedenunder, og det er en stejl og vanskelig opstigning, men de fleste rimeligt fit personer bør være i stand til at gøre det i omkring 45 minutter.

source_text: Stone steps are laid along most of the path, and in the steeper sections steel cables provide a supporting handrail.
target_text: De fleste af stien er bygget af sten, og i de stejlere sektioner er der stålkabler, der understøtter stien.

source_text: That said, expect to be out of breath, and take care in the steeper portions, especially when wet, as it can become dangerous quickly.
target_text: Når det er sagt, skal du forvente at være udåndet, og vær forsigtig i de stejlere dele, især når det er vådt, da det hurtigt kan blive farligt.

source_text: There's a tiny cave near the top that must be passed through, it is quite low and a rather tight squeeze.
target_text: Der er en lille hul tæt på toppen, der skal passeres igennem, det er ret lavt og en temmelig tæt klemme.

source_text: Seeing the sites and wildlife of the Galapagos is best done by boat, just as Charles Darwin did it in 1835.
target_text: Det er bedst at besøge Galapagos' naturområder og dyreliv med båd, ligesom Charles Darwin gjorde det i 1835.

source_text: Over 60 cruise ships ply the Galapagos waters - ranging in size from 8 to 100 passengers.
target_text: Over 60 krydstogtskibe sejler i Galapagos-vandene - alt fra 8 til 100 passagerer.

source_text: Most people book their place well in advance (as the boats are usually full during the high season).
target_text: De fleste reserverer deres plads godt i forvejen (da bådene normalt er fyldte i højsæsonen).

source_text: Be sure the agent through whom you book is a Galapagos specialist with a good knowledge of a wide variety of ships.
target_text: Sørg for, at den agent, du booker gennem, er en Galapagos-specialist med god kendskab til en bred vifte af skibe.

source_text: This will ensure that your particular interests and/or constraints are matched with the ship most suitable to them.
target_text: Dette vil sikre, at dine særlige interesser og/eller begrænsninger er i overensstemmelse med det skib, der er bedst egnet til dem.

source_text: Before the Spanish arrived in the 16th century, northern Chile was under Inca rule while the indigenous Araucanians (Mapuche) inhabited central and southern Chile.
target_text: Inden spanierne ankom i det 16. århundrede, var det nordlige Chile under inkernes styre, mens de indfødte araukanere (mapucher) beboede det centrale og sydlige Chile.

source_text: The Mapuche were also one of the last independent American indigenous groups, that were not fully absorbed into Spanish-speaking rule until after Chile's independence.
target_text: Mapuchen var også en af de sidste uafhængige indfødte grupper i Amerika, som først efter Chiles uafhængighed blev absorberet i spansktalende styre.

source_text: Although Chile declared independence in 1810 (amid the Napoleonic wars that left Spain without a functioning central government for a couple of years), decisive victory over the Spanish was not achieved until 1818.
target_text: Selv om Chile erklærede selvstændighed i 1810 (imens de napoleoniske krige forlod Spanien uden en fungerende centralregering i et par år), blev den afgørende sejr over spanierne ikke opnået før 1818.

source_text: The Dominican Republic (Spanish: República Dominicana) is a Caribbean country that occupies the eastern half of the island of Hispaniola, which it shares with Haiti
target_text: Den Dominikanske Republik (spansk: República Dominicana) er et karibisk land, der besætter den østlige halvdel af øen Hispaniola, som den deler med Haiti

source_text: Besides white sand beaches and mountain landscapes, the country is home to the oldest European city in the Americas, now part of Santo Domingo.
target_text: Udover hvide sandstrender og bjerglandskaber er landet hjemsted for den ældste europæiske by i Amerika, som nu er en del af Santo Domingo.

source_text: The island was first inhabited by the Taínos and Caribes. The Caribes were an Arawakan-speaking people who had arrived around 10,000 BCE.
target_text: Øen blev først beboet af Taínos og Caribes. Caribes var et arawak-talende folk, der var ankommet omkring 10.000 f.Kr.

source_text: Within a few short years following the arrival of European explorers, the population of Tainos had significantly been reduced by the Spanish conquerors
target_text: Inden for et par få år efter de europæiske opdagelsesrejsendes ankomst var befolkningen i Tainos blevet reduceret betydeligt af de spanske erobrere

source_text: Based on Fray Bartolomé de las Casas (Tratado de las Indias) between 1492 and 1498 the Spanish conquerors killed around 100,000 Taínos.
target_text: Baseret på Fray Bartolomé de las Casas (Tratado de las Indias) mellem 1492 og 1498 dræbte de spanske erobrere omkring 100.000 Taínos.

source_text: Jardín de la Unión. This space was built as the atrium for a 17th-century convent, of which the Templo de San Diego is the sole surviving building.
target_text: Jardín de la Unión. Dette rum blev bygget som atrium for et kloster fra det 17. århundrede, hvoraf Templo de San Diego er den eneste overlevende bygning.

source_text: It now functions as the central plaza, and always has a lot of things going on, day and night.
target_text: Det fungerer nu som den centrale plaza, og der foregår altid en masse ting, dag og nat.

source_text: There are a number of restaurants surrounding the garden, and in the afternoons and evening there free concerts are often given from the central gazebo.
target_text: Der er en række restauranter omkring haven, og om eftermiddagen og aftenen gives der ofte gratis koncerter fra den centrale gazebo.

source_text: Callejon del Beso (Alley of the Kiss). Two balconies separated by only 69 centimeters is home of an old love legend.
target_text: Callejon del Beso (Kyssens Alley) er hjemsted for en gammel kærlighedslegende.

source_text: For a few pennies some children will tell you the story.
target_text: For et par cent vil nogle børn fortælle dig historien.

source_text: Bowen Island is a popular day trip or weekend excursion offering kayaking, hiking, shops, restaurants, and more.
target_text: Bowen Island er en populær dagstur eller weekendtur, der tilbyder kajak, vandreture, butikker, restauranter og meget mere.

source_text: This authentic community is located in Howe Sound just off Vancouver, and is easily accessed via scheduled water taxis departing Granville Island in downtown Vancouver.
target_text: Dette autentiske samfund ligger i Howe Sound lige uden for Vancouver og er let tilgængeligt via vandtaxis fra Granville Island i centrum af Vancouver.

source_text: For those who enjoy outdoor activities, a trek up the Sea to Sky corridor is essential.
target_text: For dem der nyder udendørs aktiviteter er en vandring op ad Sea to Sky-korridoren afgørende.

source_text: Whistler (1.5 hour drive from Vancouver) is expensive but well-known because of the 2010 Winter Olympics.
target_text: Whistler (1.5 timers kørsel fra Vancouver) er dyrt, men velkendt på grund af vinter-OL 2010.

source_text: In the winter, enjoy some of the best skiing in North America, and in the summer try some authentic mountain biking.
target_text: Om vinteren kan du nyde nogle af de bedste skidløb i Nordamerika, og om sommeren kan du prøve nogle autentiske bjergcykler.

source_text: Permits must be reserved in advance. You must have a permit to stay overnight at Sirena.
target_text: Du skal have tilladelse til at overnatte i Sirena.

source_text: Sirena is the only ranger station that offers dormitory lodging and hot meals in addition to camping. La Leona, San Pedrillo, and Los Patos offer only camping with no food service.
target_text: Sirena er den eneste rangerstation der tilbyder sovesal og varme måltider ud over camping. La Leona, San Pedrillo og Los Patos tilbyder kun camping uden madservice.

source_text: It is possible to secure park permits directly from the Ranger Station in Puerto Jiménez, but they do not accept credit cards
target_text: Det er muligt at få parktilladelse direkte fra Ranger Station i Puerto Jiménez, men de accepterer ikke kreditkort

source_text: The Park Service (MINAE) does not issue park permits more than one month in advance of anticipated arrival.
target_text: Parkstyrelsen (MINAE) udsteder ikke parktilladelser mere end en måned forud for den forventede ankomst.

source_text: CafeNet El Sol offers a reservation service for a fee of US$30, or $10 for one-day passes; details on their Corcovado page.
target_text: CafeNet El Sol tilbyder en reservationstjeneste for et gebyr på US $ 30, eller $ 10 for en dag pass; detaljer på deres Corcovado side.

source_text: The Cook Islands are an island country in free association with New Zealand, located in Polynesia, in the middle of the South Pacific Ocean.
target_text: Cookøerne er et øland i fri association med New Zealand, beliggende i Polynesien, midt i det sydlige Stillehav.

source_text: It is an archipelago with 15 islands spread out over 2.2 million km2 of ocean.
target_text: Det er en øøgruppe med 15 øer, der strækker sig over 2,2 millioner km2 hav.

source_text: With the same time zone as Hawaii, the islands are sometimes thought of as "Hawaii down under".
target_text: Med samme tidszone som Hawaii er øerne nogle gange tænkt på som "Hawaii under".

source_text: Though smaller, it reminds some elderly visitors of Hawaii before statehood without all the large tourist hotels and other development.
target_text: Selv om det er mindre, minder det nogle ældre besøgende om Hawaii før staten blev oprettet uden alle de store turisthoteller og andre udviklinger.

source_text: The Cook Islands do not have any cities but are composed of 15 different islands. The main ones are Rarotonga and Aitutaki.
target_text: Cookøerne har ingen byer, men består af 15 forskellige øer, hvoraf de vigtigste er Rarotonga og Aitutaki.

source_text: In developed countries today, providing deluxe bed and breakfasts has been raised to a sort of art-form.
target_text: I de udviklede lande er det i dag blevet en form for kunst at tilbyde luksusbed og morgenmad.

source_text: At the top end, B&Bs obviously compete mainly on two main things: bedding and breakfast.
target_text: I den øverste ende konkurrerer B&B'er naturligvis hovedsageligt om to hoved ting: sengetøj og morgenmad.

source_text: Accordingly, at the finest such establishments one is apt to find the most luxurious bedding, maybe a handmade quilt or an antique bed.
target_text: I de fineste af disse restauranter kan man derfor finde det mest luksuriøse sengetøj, måske en håndlavet tæppe eller en gammeldags seng.

source_text: Breakfast may include seasonal delights of the region or the host's speciality dish.
target_text: Frokost kan indeholde sæsonbetonede godheder fra regionen eller værtsens specialitet.

source_text: The setting might be an historic old building with antique furnishings, manicured grounds and a swimming pool.
target_text: Det kan være en historisk gammel bygning med antikke møbler, udrustede arealer og en swimmingpool.

source_text: Getting into your own car and heading off on a long road trip has an intrinsic appeal in its simplicity.
target_text: At komme ind i din egen bil og tage af sted på en lang vejrejse har en iboende attraktion i sin enkelhed.

source_text: Unlike larger vehicles, you are probably already familiar with driving your car and know its limitations.
target_text: I modsætning til større biler er du sikkert allerede bekendt med at køre bilen og kender dens begrænsninger.

source_text: Setting up a tent on private property or in a town of any size can easily attract unwanted attention.
target_text: At sætte et telt på privat ejendom eller i en by af enhver størrelse kan let tiltrække uønsket opmærksomhed.

source_text: In short, using your car is a great way to take a road trip but seldom in itself a way to "camp".
target_text: Kort sagt, at bruge din bil er en god måde at tage en rejse på, men sjældent i sig selv en måde at "lejre".

source_text: Car camping is possible if you have a large minivan, SUV, Sedan or Station Wagon with seats that lay down.
target_text: Bilcamping er muligt, hvis du har en stor minivan, SUV, Sedan eller Station Wagon med sæder, der ligger ned.

source_text: Some hotels have a heritage from the golden age of steam railways and ocean liners; before the Second World War, in the 19th or early 20th centuries.
target_text: Nogle hoteller har en arv fra den gyldne tidsalder af dampjernbaner og havfartøjer; før Anden Verdenskrig, i det 19. eller begyndelsen af det 20. århundrede.

source_text: These hotels were where the rich and the famous of the day would stay, and often had fine dining and nightlife.
target_text: Disse hoteller var steder hvor de rige og berømte på den tid boede, og de havde ofte smukke restauranter og et godt natligt liv.

source_text: The old fashioned fittings, the lack of the latest amenities, and a certain graceful agedness are also part of their character.
target_text: De gammeldags anlæg, manglen på de nyeste bekvemmeligheder og en vis elegant alderdom er også en del af deres karakter.

source_text: While they are usually privately owned, they sometimes accommodate visiting heads of state and other dignitaries.
target_text: De er som regel privat ejendom, men nogle gange kan de rumme statsoverhoveder og andre højtstående personer.

source_text: A traveller with piles of money might consider a round the world flight, broken up with stays in many of these hotels.
target_text: En rejsende med masser af penge kan overveje at flyve rundt om i verden, hvis man ikke længere skal bo på mange af disse hoteller.

source_text: A hospitality exchange network is the organization that connects travelers with locals in the cities they are going to visit.
target_text: Et gæstfrihedsudvekslingsnetværk er den organisation, der forbinder rejsende med lokalbefolkningen i de byer, de skal besøge.

source_text: Joining such a network usually just requires filling out an online form; although some networks offer or require additional verification.
target_text: For at deltage i et sådant netværk kræves normalt blot at udfylde en online formular; selv om nogle netværk tilbyder eller kræver yderligere verifikation.

source_text: A listing of available hosts is then provided either in print and/or online, sometimes with references and reviews by other travelers.
target_text: En liste over tilgængelige værter gives derefter enten i trykt og/eller online, nogle gange med referencer og anmeldelser fra andre rejsende.

source_text: Couchsurfing was founded in January 2004 after computer programmer Casey Fenton found a cheap flight to Iceland but did not have a place to stay.
target_text: Couchsurfing blev grundlagt i januar 2004 efter at computerprogrammerende Casey Fenton fandt en billig flyvning til Island, men havde ikke et sted at bo.

source_text: He emailed students at the local university and received an overwhelming number of offers for free accommodation.
target_text: Han sendte e-mails til studerende på det lokale universitet og modtog et overvældende antal tilbud om gratis ophold.

source_text: Hostels cater primarily to young people – a typical guest is in their twenties – but you can often find older travellers there too.
target_text: Hostellerne er primært for unge  en typisk gæst er i deres tyve år  men du kan ofte finde ældre rejsende der også.

source_text: Families with children are a rare sight, but some hostels do allow them in private rooms.
target_text: Familier med børn er sjældne at se, men nogle vandrerhuse tillader dem i private værelser.

source_text: The city of Beijing in China will be the host city of the Olympic Winter Games in 2022, which will make it the first city to have hosted both the summer and winter Olympics.
target_text: Byen Beijing i Kina vil være værtsby for de Olympiske Vinterspil i 2022, hvilket vil gøre den til den første by at have vært for både sommer- og vinter-OL.

source_text: Beijing will host the opening and closing ceremonies and the indoor ice events.
target_text: Beijing vil være vært for åbnings- og afslutningsceremonierne og de indendørs isbegivenheder.

source_text: Other skiing events will be at the Taizicheng ski area in Zhangjiakou, about 220 km (140 miles) from Beijing.
target_text: Andre skidehistorier finder sted på Taizicheng-skiområdet i Zhangjiakou, ca. 220 km fra Beijing.

source_text: Most of the temples do have an Annual festival starting from November end to Mid of May, which varies according to each temple's annual calendar.
target_text: De fleste templer har en årlig festival, der begynder i slutningen af november til midten af maj, hvilket varierer afhængigt af hvert temples årlige kalender.

source_text: Most of the temple festivals is celebrated as part of temple's anniversary or presiding deity's birthday or any other major event associated with the temple.
target_text: De fleste tempelfestivaler fejres som en del af templets jubilæum eller guddommens fødselsdag eller enhver anden større begivenhed i forbindelse med templet.

source_text: Kerala's temple festivals are very interesting to see, with regular procession of decorated elephants, temple orchestra and other festivities.
target_text: Keralas tempelfestivaler er meget interessante at se, med en regelmæssig procession af dekorerede elefanter, tempelorkester og andre festligheder.

source_text: A World's Fair (commonly called World Exposition, or simply Expo) is large international festival of arts and sciences.
target_text: En World's Fair (commonly kaldet World Exposition, eller blot Expo) er en stor international kunst- og videnskabsfestival.

source_text: Participating countries present artistic and educational displays in national pavilions to showcase world issues or their country's culture and history.
target_text: De deltagende lande præsenterer kunstneriske og uddannelsesmæssige udstillinger i nationale paviljonger for at vise verdensspørgsmål eller deres lands kultur og historie.

source_text: International Horticultural Expositions are specialised events which showcase floral displays, botanical gardens and anything else to do with plants.
target_text: Internationale gartneriudstillinger er specialiserede arrangementer, der viser blomsterudstillinger, botaniske haver og alt andet, der har med planter at gøre.

source_text: Although in theory they can take place annually (so long as they are in different countries), in practice they are not.
target_text: Selv om de i teorien kan finde sted årligt (så længe de er i forskellige lande), er de i praksis ikke.

source_text: These events normally last anywhere between three and six months, and are held on sites no smaller than 50 hectares.
target_text: Disse arrangementer varer normalt mellem tre og seks måneder og finder sted på en areal på mindst 50 hektar.

source_text: There are many different film formats that have been used over the years. Standard 35 mm film (36 by 24 mm negative) is much the commonest.
target_text: Der er mange forskellige filmformater, der er blevet brugt gennem årene. Standard 35 mm film (36 x 24 mm negativ) er meget den mest almindelige.

source_text: It can usually be replenished fairly easily if you run out, and gives resolution roughly comparable to a current DSLR.
target_text: Det kan normalt genopfyldes temmelig let, hvis du løber ud, og giver en opløsning, der er omtrent sammenlignelig med et nuværende DSLR.

source_text: Some medium-format film cameras use a 6 by 6 cm format, more precisely a 56 by 56 mm negative.
target_text: Nogle mediumformatfilmkameraer bruger et 6 x 6 cm format, mere præcist et 56 x 56 mm negativ.

source_text: This gives resolution almost four times that of a 35 mm negative (3136 mm2 versus 864).
target_text: Dette giver en opløsning, der er næsten fire gange den af en 35 mm minus (3136 mm2 versus 864).

source_text: Wildlife is among the most challenging motifs for a photographer, and needs a combination of good luck, patience, experience and good equipment.
target_text: Wildlife er et af de mest udfordrende motiver for en fotograf, og det kræver en kombination af held, tålmodighed, erfaring og godt udstyr.

source_text: Wildlife photography is often taken for granted, but like photography in general, a picture is worth a thousand words.
target_text: Naturfotografering tages ofte for givet, men som fotografi generelt er et billede værd tusind ord.

source_text: Wildlife photography often requires a long telephoto lens, though things like a flock of birds or a tiny creature need other lenses.
target_text: For at fotografere vildtlevende dyr er det ofte nødvendigt med et langt teleobjektiv, selv om ting som en flok fugle eller et lille væsen har brug for andre linser.

source_text: Many exotic animals are hard to find, and parks sometimes have rules about taking photographs for commercial purposes.
target_text: Mange eksotiske dyr er svære at finde, og parker har nogle gange regler om at tage billeder til kommercielle formål.

source_text: Wild animals might either be shy or aggressive. The environment might be cold, hot, or otherwise hostile.
target_text: De vilde dyr kan være flinke eller aggressive, men miljøet kan være koldt, varmt eller fjendtligt.

source_text: The world has over 5,000 different languages, including more than twenty with 50 million or more speakers.
target_text: Verden har over 5.000 forskellige sprog, herunder mere end tyve med 50 millioner eller flere talere.

source_text: Written words are often easier to understand than spoken words, also. This is especially true of addresses, which are often difficult to pronounce intelligibly.
target_text: Skrevne ord er ofte nemmere at forstå end talte ord, og det gælder især adresser, som ofte er vanskelige at udtale forståeligt.

source_text: Many entire nations are completely fluent in English, and in even more you can expect a limited knowledge - especially among younger people.
target_text: Mange hele nationer taler helt flydende engelsk, og i endnu mere kan man forvente en begrænset viden - især blandt de yngre.

source_text: Imagine, if you will, a Mancunian, Bostonian, Jamaican and Sydneysider sitting around a table having dinner at a restaurant in Toronto.
target_text: Forestil dig, hvis du vil, en Mancunian, Bostonian, Jamaican og Sydneysider sidder omkring et bord og spiser middag på en restaurant i Toronto.

source_text: They're regaling each other with stories from their hometowns, told in their distinct accents and local argot.
target_text: De giver hinanden historier fra deres hjemby, fortalt i deres forskellige accenter og lokale argot.

source_text: Buying food in supermarkets is usually the cheapest way to get fed. Without cooking opportunities, choices are however limited to ready-made food.
target_text: At købe mad i supermarkeder er normalt den billigste måde at få mad på.

source_text: Increasingly supermarkets are getting a more varied section of ready-made food. Some even provide a microwave oven or other means to heat food.
target_text: I flere og flere supermarkeder er der flere og flere færdige madvarer, og nogle tilbyder endda en mikrobølgeovn eller andre midler til opvarmning af mad.

source_text: In some countries or types of stores there is at least one on-site restaurant, often a rather informal one with affordable prices.
target_text: I nogle lande eller typer af butikker findes der mindst én restaurant på stedet, ofte en temmelig uformel restaurant med overkommelige priser.

source_text: Make and carry copies of your policy and your insurer's contact details with you.
target_text: Tag kopier af forsikringen og forsikringsselskabets kontaktoplysninger med dig.

source_text: They need to show the insurer's e-mail address and international phone numbers for advice/authorizations and making claims.
target_text: De skal vise forsikringsselskabets e-mailadresse og internationale telefonnumre til rådgivning/tilladelse og krav.

source_text: Have another copy in your luggage and online (e-mail to yourself with attachment, or stored in the "cloud").
target_text: Hav en anden kopi i bagagen og på nettet (e-mail til dig selv med vedhæftet eller opbevar i "cloud").

source_text: If traveling with a laptop or tablet, store a copy in its memory or disc (accessible without the internet).
target_text: Hvis du rejser med en bærbar computer eller tablet, skal du gemme en kopi på dennes hukommelse eller diske (tilgængelig uden internet).

source_text: Also give policy/contact copies to traveling companions and relatives or friends back home willing to help.
target_text: Giv også politik/kontaktkopier til rejsende venner og slægtninge eller venner der er villige til at hjælpe.

source_text: Moose (also known as elk) aren't inherently aggressive, but will defend themselves if they perceive a threat.
target_text: Moose (også kendt som elk) er ikke i sig selv aggressive, men vil forsvare sig selv, hvis de opfatter en trussel.

source_text: When people don't see moose as potentially dangerous, they may approach too closely and put themselves at risk.
target_text: Når folk ikke ser alge som potentielt farligt, kan de komme for tæt på og sætte sig selv i fare.

source_text: Drink alcoholic drinks with moderation. Alcohol affects everyone differently, and knowing your limit is very important.
target_text: Alcohol påvirker alle forskelligt, og det er meget vigtigt at man kender sin grænse.

source_text: Possible long term health events from excessive drinking can include liver damage and even blindness and death. The potential danger is increased when consuming illegally produced alcohol.
target_text: De langvarige sundhedsmæssige hændelser som følge af overdreven drikke kan omfatte leverbeskadigelse og endda blindhed og død.

source_text: Illegal spirits can contain various dangerous impurities including methanol, which can cause blindness or death even in small doses.
target_text: Illegal spiritus kan indeholde forskellige farlige urenheder, herunder methanol, som kan forårsage blindhed eller død selv i små doser.

source_text: Eyeglasses can be cheaper in a foreign country, especially in low-income countries where labour costs are lower.
target_text: Briller kan være billigere i et fremmedland, især i lavindkomstlande, hvor arbejdskraftomkostningerne er lavere.

source_text: Consider getting an eye exam at home, especially if insurance covers it, and bringing the prescription along to be filed elsewhere.
target_text: Tænk på at tage en øjenundersøgelse derhjemme, især hvis forsikringen dækker den, og tage receptet med til at arkivere et andet sted.

source_text: High-end brand-name frames available in such areas may have two problems; some may be knock-offs, and the real imported ones may be more expensive than at home.
target_text: Der kan være to problemer med high-end-mærker, der findes på sådanne områder: nogle kan være overskydende, og de rigtige importprodukter kan være dyrere end hjemme.

source_text: Coffee is one of the world's most traded commodities, and you can probably find many types in your home region.
target_text: Kaffe er en af verdens mest handlede varer, og du kan sandsynligvis finde mange typer i din hjemland.

source_text: Nevertheless, there are many distinctive ways of drinking coffee around the world that are worth experiencing.
target_text: Men der er mange forskellige måder at drikke kaffe på i hele verden, som er værd at opleve.

source_text: Canyoning (or: canyoneering) is about going in a bottom of a canyon, which is either dry or full of water.
target_text: Canyoning (eller: canyoneering) handler om at gå i bunden af en canyon, som enten er tør eller fuld af vand.

source_text: Canyoning combines elements from swimming, climbing and jumping--but requires relatively little training or physical shape to get started (compared to rock climbing, scuba diving or alpine skiing, for example).
target_text: Canyoning kombinerer elementer fra svømning, klatring og hoppe - men kræver relativt lidt træning eller fysisk form for at komme i gang (i forhold til klippeklatring, dykning eller alpine ski, for eksempel).

source_text: Hiking is an outdoor activity which consists of walking in natural environments, often on hiking trails.
target_text: Vandretur er en udendørs aktivitet, der består af at gå i naturlige omgivelser, ofte på vandreturer.

source_text: Day hiking involves distances of less than a mile up to longer distances that can be covered in a single day.
target_text: Dagevandring indebærer afstande på mindre end en kilometer, men også længere afstande, der kan løbes på en enkelt dag.

source_text: For a day hike along an easy trail little preparations are needed, and any moderately fit person can enjoy them.
target_text: For en dagstur langs en nem sti er der brug for små forberedelser, og enhver i moderat form kan nyde dem.

source_text: Families with small children may need more preparations, but a day outdoors is easily possible even with babies and pre-school children.
target_text: Familier med små børn har måske brug for flere forberedelser, men en dag udendørs er let mulig selv med spædbørn og børn før skoletid.

source_text: Internationally, there are nearly 200 running tour organizations. Most of them operate independently.
target_text: Internationalt er der næsten 200 turorganisationer, hvoraf de fleste er uafhængige.

source_text: The Global Running Tours successor, Go Running Tours networks dozens of sightrunning providers on four continents.
target_text: Global Running Tours' efterfølger, Go Running Tours, har netværk af dusinvis af udbydere på fire kontinenter.

source_text: With roots in Barcelona's Running Tours Barcelona and Copenhagen's Running Copenhagen, it was quickly joined by Running Tours Prague based in Prague and others.
target_text: Med rødder i Barcelonas Running Tours Barcelona og Københavns Running Copenhagen, blev det hurtigt tilsluttet af Running Tours Prague baseret i Prag og andre.

source_text: There are many things you have to take into consideration before and when you travel somewhere.
target_text: Der er mange ting man skal overveje før og når man rejser et sted.

source_text: When you travel, expect things not to be like they are "back home". Manners, laws, food, traffic, lodging, standards, language and so on will to some extent differ from where you live.
target_text: Når du rejser, skal du forvente at tingene ikke bliver som "hjemmefra". Adfærd, love, mad, trafik, opholdssted, standarder, sprog osv. vil til en vis grad være anderledes end hvor du bor.

source_text: This is something you always need to keep in mind, to avoid disappointment or perhaps even distaste over local ways to do things.
target_text: Det er noget man altid skal huske på for at undgå skuffelse eller måske endda afsky for de lokale måder at gøre ting på.

source_text: Travel agencies have been around since the 19th century. A travel agent is usually a good option for a journey which extends beyond a traveller's previous experience of nature, culture, language or low-income countries.
target_text: Reisebyråer har eksisteret siden det 19. århundrede. En rejsebyrå er normalt en god mulighed for en rejse, der strækker sig ud over en rejsendes tidligere erfaring med natur, kultur, sprog eller lavindkomstlande.

source_text: Although most agencies are willing to take on most regular bookings, many agents specialise in particular types of travel, budget ranges or destinations.
target_text: Selv om de fleste agenturer er villige til at foretage de fleste regelmæssige reservationer, er mange agenter specialiseret i bestemte typer rejser, budgetområder eller destinationer.

source_text: It can be better to use an agent who frequently books similar trips to yours.
target_text: Det kan være bedre at bruge en agent, der ofte bestiller lignende rejser som dine.

source_text: Take a look at what trips the agent is promoting, whether on a website or in a shop window.
target_text: Se på, hvilke ture agenten markedsfører, enten på et websted eller i et vindue.

source_text: If you want to see the world on the cheap, for necessity, lifestyle or challenge, there are some ways to do that.
target_text: Hvis du vil se verden billig, for nødvendighed, livsstil eller udfordring, er der nogle måder at gøre det på.

source_text: Basically, they fall into two categories: Either work while you travel or try and limit your expenses. This article is focused on the latter.
target_text: De er i grunden inddelt i to kategorier: Enten arbejde mens du rejser eller forsøge at begrænse dine udgifter.

source_text: For those willing to sacrifice comfort, time and predictability to push expenses down close to zero, see minimum budget travel.
target_text: For dem, der er villige til at ofre komfort, tid og forudsigelighed for at skubbe udgifterne ned til næsten nul, se minimumsbudgetrejs.

source_text: The advice assumes that travellers do not steal, trespass, participate in the illegal market, beg, or otherwise exploit other people for their own gain.
target_text: I denne vejledning antages det at rejsende ikke stjæler, overtræder, deltager i ulovlige markeder, tigger eller på anden måde udnytter andre til egen gavn.

source_text: An immigration checkpoint is usually the first stop when disembarking from a plane, a ship, or another vehicle.
target_text: Et indvandrerkontrolsted er normalt det første stoppested, når man stiger fra et fly, et skib eller et andet køretøj.

source_text: In some cross-border trains inspections are done on the running train and you should have valid ID with you when boarding one of those trains.
target_text: I nogle grænseoverskridende tog foretages inspektioner på det løbende tog, og du skal have gyldig ID med dig, når du går ombord på et af disse tog.

source_text: On night sleeper trains, passports may be collected by the conductor so that you do not have your sleep interrupted.
target_text: På natstogene kan passet blive indhentet af dirigenten, så du ikke bliver afbrudt af søvn.

source_text: Registration is an additional requirement for the visa process. In some countries, you must register your presence and address where you are staying with the local authorities.
target_text: I nogle lande skal du registrere din tilstedeværelse og din adresse hos de lokale myndigheder.

source_text: This might require filling out a form with the local police or a visit to the immigration offices.
target_text: Det kan kræve at du udfylder en formular hos den lokale politi eller besøger indvandringskontoret.

source_text: In many countries with such a law, local hotels will handle the registration (make sure to ask).
target_text: I mange lande med en sådan lov håndterer lokale hoteller registreringen (gør dig sikker på at spørge).

source_text: In other cases, only those staying outside of tourist accommodations need to register.  However, this makes the law much more obscure, so find out beforehand.
target_text: I andre tilfælde er det kun dem, der bor uden for turistboliger, der skal registrere sig.

source_text: Architecture is concerned with the design and construction of buildings. The architecture of a place is often a tourist attraction in its own right.
target_text: Arkitektur beskæftiger sig med design og konstruktion af bygninger. Arkitektur af et sted er ofte en turistattraktion i sig selv.

source_text: Many buildings are quite beautiful to look at and the view from a tall building or from a cleverly-positioned window can be a beauty to behold.
target_text: Mange bygninger er ganske smukke at se på, og udsigten fra en høj bygning eller fra et klogt placeret vindue kan være smukt at se på.

source_text: Architecture overlaps considerably with other fields including urban planning, civil engineering, decorative arts, interior design and landscape design.
target_text: Arkitekturen overlapper betydeligt med andre områder, herunder byplanlægning, civilteknik, dekorative kunst, interiørdesign og landskabsdesign.

source_text: Given how remote many of the pueblos are, you won't be able to find a significant amount of nightlife without traveling to Albuquerque or Santa Fe.
target_text: I betragtning af hvor fjernt de fleste pueblos er, vil du ikke være i stand til at finde en betydelig mængde af natlivet uden at rejse til Albuquerque eller Santa Fe.

source_text: However, nearly all of the casinos listed above serve drinks, and several of them bring in name-brand entertainment (primarily the large ones immediately surrounding Albuquerque and Santa Fe).
target_text: Men næsten alle de casinoer, der er opført ovenfor, serverer drikkevarer, og flere af dem bringer navnebrand underholdning (primært de store, der umiddelbart omgiver Albuquerque og Santa Fe).

source_text: Beware: small-town bars here are not always good places for the out-of-state visitor to hang out.
target_text: Pas på: Barer i småbyer her er ikke altid gode steder for en udenlandsk gæst at henge ud.

source_text: For one thing, northern New Mexico has significant problems with drunk driving, and the concentration of intoxicated drivers is high close to small-town bars.
target_text: For det første har det nordlige New Mexico betydelige problemer med at køre beruset, og koncentrationen af berusede chauffører er høj i nærheden af småbybarer.

source_text: Unwanted murals or scribble is known as graffiti.
target_text: Uønskede vægmalerier er kendt som graffiti.

source_text: While it's far from a modern phenomenon, most people probably associate it with youth vandalizing public and private property using spray paint.
target_text: Selv om det er langt fra et moderne fænomen, forbinder de fleste det sandsynligvis med unge der vandaliserer offentlig og privat ejendom ved hjælp af sprayfarve.

source_text: However, nowadays there are established graffiti artists, graffiti events and "legal" walls. Graffiti paintings in this context often resemble artworks rather than illegible tags.
target_text: I dag er der dog etablerede graffiti kunstnere, graffiti arrangementer og "legale" vægge.

source_text: Boomerang throwing is a popular skill that many tourists want to acquire.
target_text: Boomerangkast er en populær færdighed, som mange turister ønsker at erhverve.

source_text: If you want to learn throwing a boomerang that comes back to your hand, make sure you have a suitable boomerang for returning.
target_text: Hvis du vil lære at kaste en boomerang, der kommer tilbage til din hånd, sørg for at du har en passende boomerang til at vende tilbage.

source_text: Most boomerangs available in Australia are in fact non-returning. It is best for beginners to not try throwing in windy
target_text: De fleste boomeranger, der findes i Australien, er faktisk ikke tilbagevendende.

source_text: A Hangi Meal is cooked in a hot pit in the ground.
target_text: Et Hangi-måltid er tilberedt i en varm hul i jorden.

source_text: The pit is either heated with hot stones from a fire, or in some places geothermal heat makes areas of ground naturally hot.
target_text: Gruden opvarmes enten med varme sten fra en brand, eller på nogle steder gør geotermisk varme områder af jorden naturligt varme.

source_text: The hangi is often used to cook a traditional roast style dinner.
target_text: Hongien bruges ofte til at lave en traditionel stegt middag.

source_text: Several places in Rotorua offer geothermal hangi, while other hangi can be sampled in Christchurch, Wellington and elsewhere.
target_text: Flere steder i Rotorua tilbyder geotermiske hangi, mens andre hangi kan prøves i Christchurch, Wellington og andre steder.

source_text: MetroRail has two classes on commuter trains in and around Cape Town: MetroPlus (also called First Class) and Metro (called Third Class).
target_text: MetroRail har to klasser på pendeltog i og omkring Cape Town: MetroPlus (også kaldet Første Klasse) og Metro (kaldt Tredje Klasse).

source_text: MetroPlus is more comfortable and less crowded but slightly more expensive, though still cheaper than normal metro tickets in Europe.
target_text: MetroPlus er mere behageligt og mindre overfyldt, men lidt dyrere, men stadig billigere end normale metrobilletter i Europa.

source_text: Every train has both MetroPlus and Metro coaches; the MetroPlus coaches are always on the end of the train nearest Cape Town.
target_text: Hvert tog har både MetroPlus og Metro-busser; MetroPlus-busserne er altid på ende af toget nærmest Cape Town.

source_text: Carrying for others - Never let your bags out of your sight, especially when you are crossing international borders.
target_text: At bære for andre - Lad aldrig dine tasker gå ud af synet, især når du krydser internationale grænser.

source_text: You could find yourself being used as a drug carrier without your knowledge, which will land you in a great deal of trouble.
target_text: Du kan blive brugt til at transportere stoffer uden din viden, hvilket vil bringe dig i store problemer.

source_text: This includes waiting in line, as drug-sniffing dogs could be used at any time without notice.
target_text: Dette omfatter at vente i kø, da hunder, der sniffer stoffer, kunne blive brugt til enhver tid uden varsel.

source_text: Some countries have exceedingly draconian punishments even for first time offenses; these can include prison sentences of over 10 years or death.
target_text: Nogle lande har yderst strenge straffe, selv for første gang begået overtrædelser; disse kan omfatte fængselsstraffer på over 10 år eller dødsstraf.

source_text: Unattended bags are a target for theft and can also attract attention from authorities wary of bomb threats.
target_text: Unattended tasker er et mål for tyveri og kan også tiltrække opmærksomheden fra myndigheder som er bange for bomber truer.

source_text: At home, due to this constant exposure to the local germs, odds are very high that you're already immune to them.
target_text: Hjemme, på grund af denne konstante eksponering for de lokale bakterier, er chancerne meget høje for at du allerede er immun mod dem.

source_text: But in other parts of the world, where the bacteriological fauna are new to you, you're far more likely to run into problems.
target_text: Men i andre dele af verden, hvor bakteriologiske dyr er nye for dig, er du meget mere tilbøjelig til at komme i problemer.

source_text: Also, in warmer climates bacteria both grow more quickly and survive longer outside the body.
target_text: I varmere klimaer vokser bakterierne også hurtigere og lever længere uden for kroppen.

source_text: Thus the scourges of Delhi Belly, the Pharaoh's Curse, Montezuma's Revenge, and their many friends.
target_text: Således de plager af Delhi Belly, Faraos forbandelse, Montezumas hævn og deres mange venner.

source_text: As with respiratory problems in colder climates, intestinal problems in hot climates are fairly common and in most cases are distinctly annoying but not really dangerous.
target_text: Ligesom respiratoriske problemer i kaldere klimaer er tarmproblemer i varme klimaer ganske almindelige og i de fleste tilfælde tydeligt irriterende, men ikke særlig farlige.

source_text: If traveling in a developing country for the first time – or in a new part of the world – don't underestimate the potential culture shock.
target_text: Hvis du rejser til et udviklingsland for første gang  eller til en ny del af verden  undervurder ikke det potentielle kulturchock.

source_text: Many a stable, capable traveler has been overcome by the newness of developing world travel, where many little cultural adjustments can add up quickly.
target_text: Mange af de stabile, dygtige rejsende er blevet overvundet af den nye udvikling af verdensrejser, hvor mange små kulturelle tilpasninger hurtigt kan tilføjes.

source_text: Especially in your initial days, consider splurging on Western-style and -quality hotels, food, and services to help acclimatize.
target_text: Især i de første dage kan du overveje at bruge penge på hoteller, mad og tjenester i vestlig stil.

source_text: Do not sleep on a mattress or pad on the ground in areas where you do not know the local fauna.
target_text: Sov ikke på en madrasse eller på en pad på jorden i områder hvor du ikke kender den lokale fauna.

source_text: If you are going to camp out, bring a camp cot or hammock to keep you away from snakes, scorpions and such.
target_text: Hvis du skal campere, skal du tage med en campingkæde eller en hængekæde for at holde dig væk fra slanger, skorpioner og lignende.

source_text: Fill your home with a rich coffee in the morning and some relaxing chamomile tea at night.
target_text: Fyll dit hjem med en rig kaffe om morgenen og en afslappende kamillete om aftenen.

source_text: When you're on a staycation, you have the time to treat yourself and take a few extra minutes to brew up something special.
target_text: Når du er på ferie, har du tid til at passe dig selv og tage et par ekstra minutter til at lave noget særligt.

source_text: If you're feeling more adventurous, take the opportunity to juice or blend up some smoothies:
target_text: Hvis du føler dig mere eventyrlig, kan du bruge lejligheden til juice eller bland nogle smoothies:

source_text: maybe you'll discover a simple beverage that you can make for breakfast when you're back to your daily routine.
target_text: Måske vil du opdage en simpel drink, som du kan lave til morgenmad, når du er tilbage til din daglige rutine.

source_text: If you live in a city with a varied drinking culture, go to bars or pubs in neighborhoods you don't frequent.
target_text: Hvis du bor i en by med en varieret drikkekultur, skal du gå til barer eller pubs i nabolag du ikke ofte besøger.

source_text: For those unfamiliar with medical jargon, the words infectious and contagious have distinct meanings.
target_text: For dem der ikke kender medicinsk jargon, har ordene smitsomme og smitsomme forskellige betydninger.

source_text: An infectious disease is one that is caused by a pathogen, such as a virus, bacterium, fungus or other parasites.
target_text: En smitsom sygdom er en sygdom forårsaget af et patogen, f.eks. et virus, bakterier, svampe eller andre parasitter.

source_text: A contagious disease is a disease which is easily transmitted by being in the vicinity of an infected person.
target_text: En smitsom sygdom er en sygdom, der let overføres ved at være i nærheden af en inficeret person.

source_text: Many governments require visitors entering, or residents leaving, their countries to be vaccinated for a range of diseases.
target_text: Mange regeringer kræver, at besøgende, der kommer ind eller rejser fra deres land, skal vaccineres mod en række sygdomme.

source_text: These requirements may often depend on what countries a traveller has visited or intends to visit.
target_text: Disse krav afhænger ofte af, hvilke lande en rejsende har besøgt eller har til hensigt at besøge.

source_text: One of strong points of Charlotte, North Carolina, is that it has an abundance of high-quality options for families.
target_text: Et af de stærke punkter ved Charlotte i North Carolina er at der er masser af gode muligheder for familier.

source_text: Residents from other areas often cite family-friendliness as a primary reason for moving there, and visitors often find the city easy to enjoy with children around.
target_text: Beboere fra andre områder nævner ofte familievenlighed som hovedårsagen til at flytte derhen, og besøgende finder det ofte nemt at nyde byen med børn omkring.

source_text: In the past 20 years, the amount of child-friendly options in Uptown Charlotte has grown exponentially.
target_text: I de sidste 20 år er antallet af børnevenlige muligheder i Uptown Charlotte vokset eksponentielt.

source_text: Taxis are not generally used by families in Charlotte, though they can be of some use in certain circumstances.
target_text: Taxier bruges generelt ikke af familier i Charlotte, selv om de kan være til nogen nytte under visse omstændigheder.

source_text: There is a surcharge for having more than 2 passengers, so this option might be more expensive than necessary.
target_text: Der er et tillægsgebyr for mere end to passagerer, så denne mulighed kan være dyrere end nødvendigt.

source_text: Antarctica is the coldest place on Earth, and surrounds the South Pole.
target_text: Antarktis er det koldeste sted på Jorden og omgiver Sydpolen.

source_text: Tourist visits are costly, demand physical fitness, can only take place in summer Nov-Feb, and are largely limited to the Peninsula, Islands and Ross Sea.
target_text: Turisternes besøg er dyre, kræver fysisk fitness, kan kun finde sted om sommeren november-februar, og er i høj grad begrænset til halvøen, øerne og Rosshavet.

source_text: A couple of thousand staff live here in summer in some four dozen bases mostly in those areas; a small number stay over winter.
target_text: Et par tusind ansatte bor her om sommeren i ca. fire dusin baser hovedsageligt i disse områder; et lille antal bliver over vinteren.

source_text: Inland Antarctica is a desolate plateau covered by 2-3 km of ice.
target_text: Inland Antarktis er et øde plateau dækket af 2-3 km is.

source_text: Occasional specialist air tours go inland, for mountaineering or to reach the Pole, which has a large base.
target_text: Af og til går specialiserede flyturer ind i landet, til bjergbestigning eller til at nå Polen, som har en stor base.

source_text: The South Pole Traverse (or Highway) is a 1600 km trail from McMurdo Station on the Ross Sea to the Pole.
target_text: South Pole Traverse (eller Highway) er en 1600 km vej fra McMurdo Station på Rosshavet til Pole.

source_text: It's compacted snow with crevasses filled in and marked by flags. It can only be traveled by specialized tractors, hauling sleds with fuel and supplies.
target_text: Det er trykt sne med sprækker fyldt og markeret med flag. Det kan kun transporteres af specialiserede traktorer, der slæber med brændstof og forsyninger.

source_text: These aren't very nimble so the trail has to take a long swerve around the Transantarctic Mountains to come onto the plateau.
target_text: De er ikke meget fleksible, så sporet skal gå langt rundt i Transantarktiske bjerge for at komme op på plateauet.

source_text: The most common cause for accidents in winter is slippery roads, pavements (sidewalks) and especially steps.
